1
00:02:15,677 --> 00:02:18,555
Senator, we're making
our final approach
into Coruscant.

2
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:20,390
Very good, Lieutenant.

3
00:03:02,766 --> 00:03:04,601
[ Droid Beeping ]

4
00:03:11,108 --> 00:03:14,069
[ Grunts ]
We made it.

5
00:03:17,865 --> 00:03:19,366
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>I guess I was wrong.</i>

6
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:21,785
There was no danger at all.

7
00:03:41,013 --> 00:03:42,222
Corde.

8
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:46,226
Milady, I'm so sorry.

9
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:49,479
<i>I've failed you, Senator.</i>

10
00:03:49,730 --> 00:03:50,814
No.

11
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:56,111
Milady, you're still
in danger here.

12
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:06,330
I shouldn't have
come back.
This vote is very important.

13
00:04:06,413 --> 00:04:10,125
You did your duty.
Corde did hers. Now, come.

14
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,213
Senator Amidala, please.

15
00:04:25,015 --> 00:04:26,725
I don't know
how much longer

16
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:29,353
I can hold off the vote,
my friends.

17
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:32,523
More and more
star systems are joining
the separatists.

18
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:36,026
If they do break away--
I will not let
this Republic...

19
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:39,863
that has stood
for a thousand years
be split in two.

20
00:04:39,947 --> 00:04:42,783
My negotiations
will not fail.

21
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:47,746
<i>If they do, you must realize</i>
<i>there aren't enough Jedi</i>
<i>to protect the Republic.</i>

22
00:04:48,497 --> 00:04:51,250
We're keepers of the peace,
not soldiers.

23
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:54,294
<i>Master Yoda.</i>

24
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:58,298
Do you think
it will really come to war?

25
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:04,054
Hmm, the dark side
clouds everything.

26
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:09,142
Impossible to see
the future is.

27
00:05:09,351 --> 00:05:10,769
The Loyalist Committee
has arrived, Your Honor.

28
00:05:10,853 --> 00:05:13,647
[ Speaking Huttese ]

29
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:16,942
<i>Good.</i>
[ Huttese ]

30
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:19,319
Send them in.

31
00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:22,823
<i>We will discuss</i>
<i>this matter later.</i>

32
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:31,081
Senator Amidala,
your tragedy on
the landing platform--

33
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:33,083
terrible.

34
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:36,920
Seeing you alive brings
warm feelings to my heart.

35
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:39,631
Do you have any idea
who was behind this attack?

36
00:05:40,132 --> 00:05:44,344
Our intelligence points
to disgruntled spice miners
on the moons of Naboo.

37
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:47,431
I think that
Count Dooku was behind it.

38
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:51,435
He is a political idealist,
not a murderer.

39
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:54,438
You know, milady,
Count Dooku was once a Jedi.

40
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:57,858
He couldn't
assassinate anyone.
It's not in his character.

41
00:05:58,192 --> 00:06:00,777
<i>But for certain,</i>
<i>Senator,</i>

42
00:06:00,861 --> 00:06:04,781
in grave danger you are.

43
00:06:05,866 --> 00:06:08,577
Master Jedi,
may I suggest...

44
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:10,621
the senator be placed...

45
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:12,998
under the protection
of your graces.

46
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:16,251
Do you really think
that's a wise decision
under these stressful times?

47
00:06:16,335 --> 00:06:18,378
Chancellor,
if I may comment,
I do not believe--

48
00:06:18,462 --> 00:06:21,298
The situation
is that serious?

49
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:23,342
No, but I do, Senator.

50
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:26,803
<i>I realize all too well</i>
<i>that additional security...</i>

51
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:29,306
<i>might be</i>
<i>disruptive for you,</i>

52
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:33,352
<i>but perhaps someone</i>
<i>you're familiar with.</i>

53
00:06:33,435 --> 00:06:37,314
An old friend,
like Master Kenobi.

54
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:39,691
<i>That's possible.</i>

55
00:06:39,775 --> 00:06:42,694
He's just returned
from a border dispute
on Ansion.

56
00:06:43,654 --> 00:06:45,822
Do it for me, milady.
Please?

57
00:06:45,948 --> 00:06:48,408
<i>The thought</i>
<i>of losing you...</i>

58
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:52,037
is unbearable.

59
00:06:52,246 --> 00:06:55,415
I will have Obi-Wan
report to you immediately,
milady.

60
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:58,627
<i>[ Senator Amidala ]</i>
<i>Thank you, Master Windu.</i>

61
00:07:07,678 --> 00:07:10,222
You seem a little on edge.

62
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:12,516
Not at all.
I haven't felt you
this tense...

63
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,810
since we fell
into that nest of gundarks.

64
00:07:14,893 --> 00:07:17,855
[ Scoffs ]
You fell into
that nightmare, Master,

65
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:20,774
and I rescued you,
remember?

66
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:23,944
Oh... yes.

67
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:25,779
[ Laughing ]

68
00:07:25,863 --> 00:07:27,447
[ Chuckles ]

69
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:32,494
You're sweating. Relax.
Take a deep breath.

70
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:35,664
I haven't seen her
in ten years, Master.

71
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:53,056
Obi? Obi!

72
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:55,475
Mesa so smilen
to seein yousa!

73
00:07:55,559 --> 00:07:59,021
Good to see you again,
Jar Jar.
<i>Senator Padme.</i>

74
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:02,691
Mesa palos here!
Lookie, lookie, Senator.

75
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:04,860
<i>Desa Jedi arriven.</i>

76
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:12,159
It's a great pleasure
to see you again, milady.

77
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:14,786
It has been far too long,
Master Kenobi.

78
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:19,208
Ani? My goodness,
you've grown.

79
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:23,462
So have you.
Grown more beautiful,
I mean.

80
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:26,298
Well, f-for a senator,
I mean.

81
00:08:28,509 --> 00:08:31,720
Ani, you'll always be
that little boy I knew
on Tatooine.

82
00:08:33,222 --> 00:08:36,725
Our presence here
will be invisible, milady,
I can assure you.

83
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:39,269
I'm Captain Typho
of Her Majesty's
security service.

84
00:08:39,353 --> 00:08:41,480
Queen Jamillia
has been informed
of your assignment.

85
00:08:41,563 --> 00:08:43,732
I am grateful you are here,
Master Kenobi.

86
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:46,610
The situation is
more dangerous than
the senator will admit.

87
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,446
I don't need more security.
I need answers.

88
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:51,782
I want to know
who's trying to kill me.

89
00:08:51,865 --> 00:08:53,617
We are here
to protect you, Senator,

90
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:55,577
not to start
an investigation.

91
00:08:55,661 --> 00:08:58,163
We will find out
who's trying
to kill you, Padme.

92
00:08:58,247 --> 00:09:01,375
I promise you.
We will not exceed
our mandate,

93
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,126
my young Padawan learner.

94
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:06,004
I meant that
in the interest of
protecting her, Master.

95
00:09:06,088 --> 00:09:08,632
<i>We will not go through</i>
<i>this exercise again,</i>
<i>Anakin,</i>

96
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:11,552
and you will
pay attention to my lead.
Why?

97
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:12,928
What?

98
00:09:14,763 --> 00:09:18,392
Why else do you think
we were assigned to her
if not to find the killer?

99
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:21,770
Protection is a job
for local security,
not Jedi.

100
00:09:21,854 --> 00:09:24,857
It's overkill, Master.
Investigation is implied
in our mandate.

101
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:28,235
We will do
exactly as the council
has instructed.

102
00:09:30,654 --> 00:09:33,740
And you will learn
your place, young one.

103
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:39,162
Perhaps with merely
your presence...

104
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:42,249
the mystery surrounding
this threat will be revealed.

105
00:09:42,332 --> 00:09:44,501
Now, if you'll excuse me,

106
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:46,920
I will retire.

107
00:09:48,505 --> 00:09:50,465
I know I'll feel better
having you here.

108
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:52,176
I'll have an officer
stationed on every floor,

109
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:54,553
and I'll be in the control
center downstairs.

110
00:09:56,388 --> 00:09:59,558
Mesa busten wit happiness
seein yousa again, Ani.

111
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:02,769
<i>She hardly even</i>
<i>recognized me, Jar Jar.</i>

112
00:10:04,271 --> 00:10:07,316
I've thought about her
every day since we parted,
and...

113
00:10:08,483 --> 00:10:10,694
she's forgotten me
completely.

114
00:10:10,777 --> 00:10:14,865
Shesa happy.
Happier den mesa seein her
in a longo time.

115
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,450
You're focusing
on the negative, Anakin.

116
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,619
Be mindful
of your thoughts.

117
00:10:19,453 --> 00:10:21,580
She was pleased to see us.

118
00:10:21,663 --> 00:10:23,373
Now, let's check
the security.

119
00:10:32,466 --> 00:10:34,718
I hit the ship,
but they used a decoy.

120
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:37,387
We'll have to try
something more subtle
this time, Zam.

121
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:40,224
My client
is getting impatient.
Take these.

122
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:42,226
Be careful.
They're very poisonous.

123
00:10:42,309 --> 00:10:45,604
Zam, there can be
no mistakes this time.

124
00:10:49,024 --> 00:10:51,443
Captain Typho has
more than enough
men downstairs.

125
00:10:51,527 --> 00:10:53,153
No assassin would
try that way.

126
00:10:54,029 --> 00:10:56,782
Any activity up here?
Quiet as a tomb.

127
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,702
I don't like just
waiting here for something
to happen to her.

128
00:11:00,786 --> 00:11:02,704
[ Beeping ]
What's going on?

129
00:11:02,788 --> 00:11:04,831
Ah, she covered
the cameras.

130
00:11:05,374 --> 00:11:07,459
I don't think
she liked me watching her.

131
00:11:07,543 --> 00:11:09,294
What is she thinking?

132
00:11:09,378 --> 00:11:12,589
She programmed R2
to warn us
if there is an intruder.

133
00:11:12,673 --> 00:11:15,300
<i>[ Obi-Wan ]</i>
<i>There are many other ways</i>
<i>to kill a senator.</i>

134
00:11:15,384 --> 00:11:16,426
<i>[ Anakin ] I know,</i>

135
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:19,763
<i>but we also want to</i>
<i>catch this assassin,</i>
<i>don't we, Master?</i>

136
00:11:21,765 --> 00:11:23,851
You're using her
as bait.

137
00:11:24,226 --> 00:11:26,144
It was her idea.

138
00:11:26,228 --> 00:11:28,772
Don't worry.
No harm will come to her.

139
00:11:28,856 --> 00:11:31,942
I can sense everything
going on in that room.

140
00:11:32,276 --> 00:11:33,694
Trust me.

141
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:35,863
It's too risky.

142
00:11:36,697 --> 00:11:40,284
Besides, your senses
aren't that attuned,
my young apprentice.

143
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:42,035
And yours are?

144
00:11:44,872 --> 00:11:46,290
Possibly.

145
00:12:00,846 --> 00:12:02,055
You look tired.

146
00:12:03,515 --> 00:12:05,475
I don't sleep well
anymore.

147
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:07,978
Because of your mother?

148
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:16,195
I don't know why
I keep dreaming about her.

149
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:20,824
Dreams pass in time.

150
00:12:22,743 --> 00:12:24,912
I'd much rather dream
about Padme.

151
00:12:25,329 --> 00:12:29,166
Just being around her
again is... intoxicating.

152
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:31,960
Be mindful
of your thoughts, Anakin.
They betray you.

153
00:12:32,044 --> 00:12:33,754
You've made a commitment
to the Jedi order,

154
00:12:33,837 --> 00:12:36,340
a commitment
not easily broken.

155
00:12:36,423 --> 00:12:38,008
And don't forget,
she's a politician,

156
00:12:38,091 --> 00:12:39,259
and they're not
to be trusted.

157
00:12:39,343 --> 00:12:41,803
<i>[ Anakin ]</i>
<i>She's not like the others</i>
<i>in the senate, Master.</i>

158
00:12:41,887 --> 00:12:43,805
<i>[ Obi-Wan ]</i>
<i>It is my experience</i>
<i>that senators...</i>

159
00:12:43,889 --> 00:12:47,809
<i>focus only on pleasing those</i>
<i>who fund their campaigns,</i>

160
00:12:47,893 --> 00:12:51,522
<i>and they're in no means</i>
<i>scared of forgetting</i>
<i>the niceties of democracy...</i>

161
00:12:51,605 --> 00:12:53,857
<i>in order to get those funds.</i>
<i>Not another lecture.</i>

162
00:12:53,941 --> 00:12:56,902
<i>At least not</i>
<i>on the economics</i>
<i>of politics.</i>

163
00:13:25,973 --> 00:13:29,309
[ R2-D2 Beeps ]

164
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:43,407
[ Beeping ]

165
00:13:52,374 --> 00:13:55,210
<i>And besides,</i>
<i>you're generalizing.</i>

166
00:13:55,294 --> 00:13:59,089
The chancellor doesn't
appear to be corrupt.
Palpatine is a politician.

167
00:13:59,173 --> 00:14:01,592
<i>[ Obi-Wan ]</i>
<i>I have observed</i>
<i>that he is very clever...</i>

168
00:14:01,675 --> 00:14:05,679
<i>in following the passions</i>
<i>and the prejudices</i>
<i>of the senators.</i>

169
00:14:05,971 --> 00:14:07,848
I think he's a good man.
My--

170
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:09,766
I sense it too.

171
00:14:17,399 --> 00:14:18,859
[ Gasps ]

172
00:14:18,942 --> 00:14:19,985
<i>[ Whirring ]</i>

173
00:14:26,408 --> 00:14:27,826
Stay here!

174
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:33,415
Are you all right, milady?

175
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:42,674
Ah!

176
00:15:07,115 --> 00:15:10,035
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>
What the--

177
00:15:13,997 --> 00:15:15,832
[ Cursing In Huttese ]

178
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,336
<i>Jedi poo doo!</i>

179
00:16:21,231 --> 00:16:23,400
What took you so long?
Oh, you know, Master.

180
00:16:23,483 --> 00:16:26,445
I couldn't find a speeder
that I really liked,
There he is.

181
00:16:26,528 --> 00:16:29,948
with the open cockpit
and the right
speed capabilities.

182
00:16:30,032 --> 00:16:31,158
If you spent as much time

183
00:16:31,241 --> 00:16:33,202
practicing your
saber techniques
as you do your wit,

184
00:16:33,285 --> 00:16:35,287
you would rival Master Yoda
as a swordsman.

185
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:39,333
I thought I already did.
Only in your mind,
my very young apprentice.

186
00:17:07,986 --> 00:17:10,239
Pull up, Anakin.
Pull up!
[ Laughing ]

187
00:17:17,454 --> 00:17:20,332
You know I don't like it
when you do that.
Sorry, Master.

188
00:17:20,415 --> 00:17:22,876
I forgot
you don't like flying.

189
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:25,796
I don't mind flying,
but what you're doing
is suicide.

190
00:17:54,074 --> 00:17:58,078
Anakin! How many times
have I told you-- Ah!--

191
00:17:58,161 --> 00:18:00,455
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!
stay away from
power couplings!

192
00:18:02,332 --> 00:18:03,417
That was good!

193
00:18:18,682 --> 00:18:21,393
Where are you going?
He went that way.

194
00:18:21,476 --> 00:18:23,353
Master,
if we keep this chase
going any longer,

195
00:18:23,437 --> 00:18:25,647
that creep is
gonna end up deep-fried,

196
00:18:25,731 --> 00:18:27,983
and, personally,
I'd very much like to
find out who he is

197
00:18:28,066 --> 00:18:30,027
and who he's working for.

198
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,946
This is a shortcut.
I think.

199
00:19:00,516 --> 00:19:02,309
Well, you've lost him.

200
00:19:02,976 --> 00:19:05,020
I'm deeply sorry, Master.

201
00:19:05,103 --> 00:19:06,980
That was some shortcut,
Anakin.

202
00:19:07,064 --> 00:19:09,066
He went completely
the other way.

203
00:19:09,149 --> 00:19:11,610
Once again
you've proved--
If you'll excuse me.

204
00:19:14,655 --> 00:19:16,073
I hate it
when he does that.

205
00:19:30,045 --> 00:19:32,631
[ Grunting ]

206
00:19:32,965 --> 00:19:34,675
<i>[ Engine Accelerating ]</i>
[ Grunting ]

207
00:20:48,248 --> 00:20:50,918
[ Shouting, Grunting ]

208
00:20:55,839 --> 00:20:58,091
[ Onlookers Murmuring ]

209
00:21:45,973 --> 00:21:47,307
Anakin!

210
00:21:47,808 --> 00:21:50,686
She went
into the club, Master.
Patience.

211
00:21:50,769 --> 00:21:52,771
Use the Force. Think.

212
00:21:52,855 --> 00:21:55,774
Sorry, Master.
He went in there to hide,
not to run.

213
00:21:55,858 --> 00:21:58,902
Yes, Master.
Next time,
try not to lose it.

214
00:21:58,986 --> 00:22:01,780
Yes, Master.
This weapon is your life.

215
00:22:02,489 --> 00:22:04,074
I try, Master.

216
00:22:04,241 --> 00:22:06,827
Why do I get the feeling
you're going to be
the death of me?

217
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:08,620
Don't say that, Master.

218
00:22:08,704 --> 00:22:10,914
You're the closest thing
I have to a father.

219
00:22:10,998 --> 00:22:14,126
Then why don't you
listen to me?
I am trying.

220
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:22,217
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

221
00:22:26,847 --> 00:22:30,642
Can you see him?
I think he is a she,

222
00:22:30,726 --> 00:22:32,561
and I think
she is a changeling.

223
00:22:34,021 --> 00:22:36,440
In that case,
be extra careful.

224
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:41,153
Go and find her.
Where are you going, Master?

225
00:22:41,236 --> 00:22:42,696
For a drink.

226
00:22:53,373 --> 00:22:54,625
Thank you.

227
00:22:56,210 --> 00:22:57,878
You wanna buy
some death sticks?

228
00:22:57,961 --> 00:22:59,880
You don't want to
sell me death sticks.

229
00:22:59,963 --> 00:23:02,674
I don't want to
sell you death sticks.
You want to go home...

230
00:23:02,758 --> 00:23:05,594
and rethink your life.
I want to go home
and rethink my life.

231
00:23:11,391 --> 00:23:15,020
<i>[ Patron Shouting In Huttese ]</i>
[ Patrons Laughing ]

232
00:23:31,578 --> 00:23:33,455
[ Cheering ]

233
00:23:45,092 --> 00:23:46,969
[ Screaming ]
[ Patrons Gasping ]

234
00:23:50,764 --> 00:23:53,267
[ Moaning, Grunting ]

235
00:23:54,268 --> 00:23:57,729
Easy. Jedi business.
Go back to your drinks.

236
00:24:02,943 --> 00:24:06,363
[ Groaning ]
Do you know who it was
you were trying to kill?

237
00:24:06,446 --> 00:24:09,241
[ Moans ] It was
a senator from Naboo.

238
00:24:09,324 --> 00:24:11,076
And who hired you?

239
00:24:11,159 --> 00:24:12,286
It was just a job.

240
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:15,455
Who hired you? Tell us.

241
00:24:17,624 --> 00:24:19,126
Tell us now!

242
00:24:20,169 --> 00:24:23,380
It was a bounty hunter
called-- [ Gagging ]

243
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:31,805
<i>Wee shahnit... sleemo.</i>

244
00:24:41,106 --> 00:24:42,691
Toxic dart.

245
00:24:53,452 --> 00:24:57,581
[ Yoda ]
Track down this bounty hunter
you must, Obi-Wan.

246
00:24:57,664 --> 00:25:01,084
Most importantly,
find out
who he's working for.

247
00:25:01,168 --> 00:25:03,003
What about
Senator Amidala?

248
00:25:03,086 --> 00:25:05,047
She will still
need protecting.

249
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:08,425
Handle that
your Padawan will.

250
00:25:10,010 --> 00:25:13,639
Anakin,
escort the senator back
to her home planet of Naboo.

251
00:25:13,722 --> 00:25:17,434
She'll be safer there.
And don't use
registered transport.

252
00:25:17,518 --> 00:25:19,520
Travel as refugees.

253
00:25:19,603 --> 00:25:22,314
As the leader
of the opposition,
it will be very difficult...

254
00:25:22,397 --> 00:25:24,858
to get Senator Amidala
to leave the capital.

255
00:25:25,776 --> 00:25:27,778
<i>Until caught</i>
<i>this killer is,</i>

256
00:25:27,861 --> 00:25:31,448
our judgment
she must respect.

257
00:25:31,532 --> 00:25:34,493
Hmm.
<i>[ Windu ]</i>
<i>Anakin, go to the senate...</i>

258
00:25:34,576 --> 00:25:37,955
and ask Chancellor Palpatine
to speak with her
about this matter.

259
00:25:47,089 --> 00:25:51,802
I will talk with her.
Senator Amidala will not
refuse an executive order.

260
00:25:51,885 --> 00:25:54,137
I know her well enough
to assure you of that.

261
00:25:54,221 --> 00:25:56,306
Thank you,
Your Excellency.

262
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:59,893
And so, they've finally
given you an assignment.

263
00:26:00,894 --> 00:26:02,896
Your patience has paid off.

264
00:26:02,980 --> 00:26:05,566
Your guidance
more than my patience.

265
00:26:06,650 --> 00:26:09,152
You don't need guidance,
Anakin.

266
00:26:10,112 --> 00:26:13,240
In time, you will learn
to trust your feelings.

267
00:26:14,908 --> 00:26:17,119
Then you will
be invincible.

268
00:26:20,414 --> 00:26:25,085
I have said it many times:
You are the most gifted Jedi
I have ever met.

269
00:26:25,169 --> 00:26:27,045
Thank you,
Your Excellency.

270
00:26:27,129 --> 00:26:30,883
I see you becoming
the greatest of all
the Jedi, Anakin,

271
00:26:30,966 --> 00:26:33,635
even more powerful
than Master Yoda.

272
00:26:38,557 --> 00:26:40,684
I am concerned
for my Padawan.

273
00:26:40,767 --> 00:26:43,520
He is not ready to be
given this assignment
on his own yet.

274
00:26:43,604 --> 00:26:46,857
[ Yoda ]
The council is confident
in its decision, Obi-Wan.

275
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:48,859
[ Windu ]
The boy has
exceptional skills.

276
00:26:48,942 --> 00:26:51,486
But he still has
much to learn, Master.

277
00:26:51,570 --> 00:26:55,032
His abilities have
made him, well, arrogant.

278
00:26:55,115 --> 00:26:57,075
Yes, yes.

279
00:26:57,159 --> 00:27:00,287
A flaw more and more
common among Jedi.

280
00:27:00,746 --> 00:27:02,039
Hmm.

281
00:27:02,122 --> 00:27:04,666
Too sure of themselves
they are.

282
00:27:04,750 --> 00:27:08,295
Even the older,
more experienced ones.

283
00:27:08,712 --> 00:27:11,882
Remember, Obi-Wan,
if the prophecy is true,

284
00:27:11,965 --> 00:27:14,218
your apprentice is
the only one who can
bring the Force

285
00:27:14,301 --> 00:27:15,719
back into balance.

286
00:27:19,806 --> 00:27:22,559
<i>[ Padme ]</i>
<i>I'm taking an extended</i>
<i>leave of absence.</i>

287
00:27:22,643 --> 00:27:25,896
<i>It will be</i>
<i>your responsibility to take</i>
<i>my place in the senate.</i>

288
00:27:25,979 --> 00:27:28,899
Representative Binks,
I know I can count on you.
Hmm?

289
00:27:28,982 --> 00:27:33,695
Mesa honored
to be taking on
dissa heavy burden.

290
00:27:33,779 --> 00:27:38,116
Mesa accept this
with muy, muy humility
and, uh--

291
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:40,911
Jar Jar, I don't wish
to hold you up.

292
00:27:40,994 --> 00:27:42,913
I'm sure you have
a great deal to do.

293
00:27:42,996 --> 00:27:46,124
Of course. Milady.

294
00:27:51,338 --> 00:27:53,173
I do not like
this idea of hiding.

295
00:27:53,841 --> 00:27:55,259
Don't worry.

296
00:27:55,342 --> 00:27:57,427
Now that
the council has ordered
an investigation,

297
00:27:57,511 --> 00:28:00,180
it won't take
Master Obi-Wan long
to find this bounty hunter.

298
00:28:00,264 --> 00:28:03,308
I haven't worked for a year
to defeat the Military
Creation Act...

299
00:28:03,392 --> 00:28:05,602
to not be here
when its fate is decided.

300
00:28:05,686 --> 00:28:10,440
Sometimes we must let go
of our pride and do
what is requested of us.

301
00:28:10,524 --> 00:28:13,110
Anakin, you've grown up.

302
00:28:14,736 --> 00:28:17,114
Master Obi-Wan
manages not to see it.

303
00:28:23,954 --> 00:28:27,999
Don't get me wrong.
Obi-Wan is a great mentor.

304
00:28:28,876 --> 00:28:31,378
As wise as
Master Yoda and...

305
00:28:31,461 --> 00:28:33,672
as powerful
as Master Windu.

306
00:28:35,883 --> 00:28:38,385
I am truly thankful
to be his apprentice.

307
00:28:40,721 --> 00:28:43,932
In some ways--
a lot of ways--

308
00:28:45,559 --> 00:28:47,603
I'm really ahead of him.

309
00:28:48,395 --> 00:28:50,230
I'm ready for the trials,

310
00:28:50,731 --> 00:28:53,734
<i>but he feels</i>
<i>that I'm too unpredictable.</i>

311
00:28:53,817 --> 00:28:55,736
<i>He won't let me move on.</i>

312
00:28:56,320 --> 00:28:58,780
That must be frustrating.
It's worse.

313
00:28:58,864 --> 00:29:01,783
He's overly critical.
He never listens.

314
00:29:01,867 --> 00:29:04,286
He-- He doesn't understand.

315
00:29:04,369 --> 00:29:05,913
It's not fair!

316
00:29:07,039 --> 00:29:11,418
All mentors have a way of
seeing more of our faults
than we would like.

317
00:29:11,502 --> 00:29:13,504
It's the only way we grow.

318
00:29:14,588 --> 00:29:16,673
[ Sighs ]
I know.

319
00:29:18,509 --> 00:29:20,010
Anakin.

320
00:29:22,346 --> 00:29:24,681
Don't try to grow up
too fast.

321
00:29:25,265 --> 00:29:27,184
But I am grown up.

322
00:29:29,102 --> 00:29:31,104
You said it yourself.

323
00:29:32,397 --> 00:29:34,358
Please don't look at me
like that.

324
00:29:35,484 --> 00:29:39,112
Why not?
It makes me
feel uncomfortable.

325
00:29:41,114 --> 00:29:42,908
Sorry, milady.

326
00:29:58,549 --> 00:30:01,176
Be safe, milady.
Thank you, Captain.

327
00:30:01,260 --> 00:30:04,221
Take good care of Dorme.
The threat's on you two now.

328
00:30:04,304 --> 00:30:06,223
He'll be safe with me.

329
00:30:10,894 --> 00:30:14,231
You'll be fine.
It's not me, milady.

330
00:30:14,314 --> 00:30:18,151
I worry about you.
What if they realize
you've left the capital?

331
00:30:19,027 --> 00:30:22,573
Well, then my Jedi protector
will have to prove
how good he is.

332
00:30:22,656 --> 00:30:24,199
Anakin.

333
00:30:24,533 --> 00:30:27,828
Don't do anything
without first consulting
either myself or the council.

334
00:30:28,328 --> 00:30:29,913
Yes, Master.

335
00:30:30,998 --> 00:30:33,709
I'll get to
the bottom of this plot
quickly, milady.

336
00:30:33,792 --> 00:30:35,586
You'll be back here
in no time.

337
00:30:35,669 --> 00:30:38,881
I'll be most grateful
for your speed,
Master Jedi.

338
00:30:38,964 --> 00:30:40,924
It's time to go.
I know.

339
00:30:41,008 --> 00:30:43,510
Anakin, may the Force
be with you.

340
00:30:43,594 --> 00:30:45,762
May the Force be
with you, Master.

341
00:30:57,024 --> 00:30:58,942
Suddenly I'm afraid.

342
00:30:59,026 --> 00:31:02,738
This is my first
assignment on my own.
I am too.

343
00:31:04,823 --> 00:31:06,909
Don't worry.
We have R2 with us.

344
00:31:06,992 --> 00:31:08,869
[ Laughing ]
[ Beeping ]

345
00:31:12,497 --> 00:31:15,792
I do hope
he doesn't try
anything foolish.

346
00:31:15,876 --> 00:31:19,505
I'd be more concerned
about her doing something
than him.

347
00:31:40,734 --> 00:31:43,195
Someone to see ya, honey!

348
00:31:43,278 --> 00:31:45,322
<i>Jedi, by the looks of him.</i>

349
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:50,244
Obi-Wan!
Hello, Dex.

350
00:31:50,953 --> 00:31:53,038
Take a seat.
I'll be right with ya.

351
00:31:55,415 --> 00:31:58,502
You wanna
cup o' jawa juice?
Oh, yes. Thank you.

352
00:32:01,755 --> 00:32:05,425
<i>Hey, old buddy!</i>

353
00:32:05,509 --> 00:32:08,762
[ Both Laughing ]

354
00:32:11,014 --> 00:32:14,518
Ohhh.
[ Coughs ]

355
00:32:14,601 --> 00:32:17,688
So, my friend,
what can I do for ya?

356
00:32:17,771 --> 00:32:19,565
You can tell me
what this is.

357
00:32:20,816 --> 00:32:24,111
Well, whattaya know!

358
00:32:24,194 --> 00:32:26,780
I ain't seen one of these
since I was prospectin'...

359
00:32:26,864 --> 00:32:30,033
<i>on Subterrel,</i>
<i>beyond the outer rim.</i>

360
00:32:30,117 --> 00:32:32,578
[ Obi-Wan ] Can you tell me
where it came from?
Thank you.

361
00:32:32,661 --> 00:32:35,747
[ Dex ]
This baby belongs
to them cloners.

362
00:32:35,831 --> 00:32:40,169
What you got here
is a Kamino saberdart.

363
00:32:40,252 --> 00:32:43,255
I wonder why
it didn't show up
in the analysis archives.

364
00:32:43,338 --> 00:32:46,508
It's these funny
little cuts on the side
that give it away.

365
00:32:46,592 --> 00:32:50,554
Those analysis droids
only focus on symbols. Huh!

366
00:32:50,637 --> 00:32:52,848
I should think that
you Jedi would have
more respect...

367
00:32:52,931 --> 00:32:55,225
for the difference
between knowledge and...

368
00:32:55,309 --> 00:32:58,228
[ Laughing ]
wisdom.

369
00:32:58,312 --> 00:33:01,815
Well, if droids could think,
there'd be none of us here,
would there?

370
00:33:03,233 --> 00:33:05,485
Kamino.
I'm not familiar with it.
Is it in the Republic?

371
00:33:05,569 --> 00:33:07,571
No, no.
It's beyond the outer rim.

372
00:33:07,654 --> 00:33:11,241
I'd say about,
uh, 12 parsecs...

373
00:33:11,325 --> 00:33:13,076
outside the Rishi Maze.

374
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:16,371
Should be easy to find,
even for those droids
in your archives.

375
00:33:16,455 --> 00:33:18,665
[ Chuckles ]

376
00:33:18,749 --> 00:33:23,629
These, uh, Kaminoans
keep to themselves.

377
00:33:23,712 --> 00:33:26,715
They're cloners.
Damn good ones too.

378
00:33:27,758 --> 00:33:31,261
Cloners. Are they friendly?
Oh, depends.

379
00:33:31,345 --> 00:33:33,263
Depends on what, Dex?

380
00:33:33,347 --> 00:33:36,099
On how good
your manners are...

381
00:33:36,183 --> 00:33:38,602
and how big your, uh,

382
00:33:38,685 --> 00:33:41,021
pocketbook is.

383
00:33:41,605 --> 00:33:42,773
[ Chuckling ]

384
00:33:45,526 --> 00:33:46,568
Hmm.

385
00:33:50,948 --> 00:33:52,574
Did you call for assistance?

386
00:33:52,658 --> 00:33:56,286
Yes, yes, I did.
Are you having a problem,
Master Kenobi?

387
00:33:56,370 --> 00:33:59,540
Yes, um, I'm looking
for a planetary system
called Kamino.

388
00:33:59,623 --> 00:34:01,959
Kamino.
It doesn't show up
on the archive charts.

389
00:34:02,042 --> 00:34:06,255
Kamino.
It's not a system
I'm familiar with.

390
00:34:06,338 --> 00:34:08,966
Are you sure you have
the right coordinates?

391
00:34:09,049 --> 00:34:12,052
According to my information,
it should appear
in this quadrant here,

392
00:34:12,135 --> 00:34:14,221
just south of
the Rishi Maze.

393
00:34:16,390 --> 00:34:18,141
[ Beeping ]

394
00:34:21,061 --> 00:34:24,523
I hate to say it,
but it looks like the system
you're searching for...

395
00:34:24,606 --> 00:34:25,983
doesn't exist.

396
00:34:26,066 --> 00:34:29,778
Impossible.
Perhaps the archives
are incomplete.

397
00:34:30,237 --> 00:34:33,031
If an item does not appear
in our records,

398
00:34:33,115 --> 00:34:35,325
it does not exist.

399
00:34:56,847 --> 00:34:59,391
Hey, you! No droids!
[ Beeping ]

400
00:34:59,474 --> 00:35:02,769
Get outta here!
[ Raspberries ]

401
00:35:07,149 --> 00:35:09,193
[ Beeping ]
Thank you, R2.

402
00:35:09,276 --> 00:35:13,822
[ Chirping ]
Must be difficult, having
sworn your life to the Jedi,

403
00:35:13,906 --> 00:35:17,910
not being able
to visit the places you like
or do the things you like.

404
00:35:17,993 --> 00:35:20,162
Or be with the people
that I love.

405
00:35:20,954 --> 00:35:22,873
Are you allowed to love?

406
00:35:22,956 --> 00:35:25,167
I thought that was
forbidden for a Jedi.

407
00:35:28,462 --> 00:35:30,964
Attachment is forbidden.

408
00:35:32,591 --> 00:35:34,426
Possession is forbidden.

409
00:35:34,510 --> 00:35:38,388
Compassion,
which I would define
as unconditional love,

410
00:35:38,472 --> 00:35:40,891
is central
to a Jedi's life.

411
00:35:43,268 --> 00:35:47,648
So you might say
that we are encouraged
to love.

412
00:35:47,981 --> 00:35:51,818
You've changed so much.
Ah, you haven't
changed a bit.

413
00:35:52,528 --> 00:35:55,531
You're exactly the way
I remember you in my dreams.

414
00:36:07,876 --> 00:36:11,672
<i>[ Yoda ]</i>
<i>Reach out.</i>
<i>Sense the Force around you.</i>

415
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:14,758
Use your feelings
you must.

416
00:36:18,846 --> 00:36:21,932
Younglings.
Younglings!

417
00:36:22,015 --> 00:36:24,434
A visitor we have.

418
00:36:24,685 --> 00:36:27,563
[ Together ]
Hello, Master Obi-Wan.

419
00:36:27,646 --> 00:36:30,732
Hello.
I'm sorry to disturb you,
Master.

420
00:36:30,816 --> 00:36:34,486
What help can I be,
Obi-Wan? Hmm?

421
00:36:34,570 --> 00:36:37,531
I'm looking for a planet
described to me
by an old friend.

422
00:36:37,614 --> 00:36:40,784
I trust him,
but the systems don't show
on the archive maps.

423
00:36:40,868 --> 00:36:45,122
Mmm. Lost a planet
Master Obi-Wan has.

424
00:36:45,205 --> 00:36:47,124
How embarrassing.
<i>[ Children Giggling ]</i>

425
00:36:47,207 --> 00:36:49,793
How embarrassing.

426
00:36:49,877 --> 00:36:52,713
Hmm? Liam, the shades.

427
00:36:54,047 --> 00:36:56,425
Gather round
the map reader.

428
00:36:56,508 --> 00:36:58,635
<i>Clear your minds...</i>

429
00:36:58,719 --> 00:37:02,347
and find Obi-Wan's
wayward planet we will.

430
00:37:03,557 --> 00:37:06,768
It ought to be... here,

431
00:37:06,852 --> 00:37:08,478
but it isn't.

432
00:37:08,562 --> 00:37:12,024
Gravity is pulling
all the stars in the area
towards this spot.

433
00:37:12,399 --> 00:37:15,861
Hmm. Gravity's silhouette
remains,

434
00:37:15,944 --> 00:37:18,989
but the star
and all the planets,

435
00:37:19,072 --> 00:37:21,116
disappeared they have.

436
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:23,118
How can this be?

437
00:37:23,410 --> 00:37:25,662
Hmm? A thought?

438
00:37:27,247 --> 00:37:31,001
<i>[ Yoda ]</i>
<i>Anyone.</i>
<i>[ Boy ] Master?</i>

439
00:37:31,084 --> 00:37:34,004
Because someone erased it
from the archive memory.

440
00:37:35,214 --> 00:37:37,090
<i>[ Yoda Chuckles ]</i>

441
00:37:37,299 --> 00:37:41,386
Truly wonderful
the mind of a child is.

442
00:37:41,470 --> 00:37:43,847
[ Chuckling ]

443
00:37:43,931 --> 00:37:46,350
The Padawan is right.

444
00:37:46,433 --> 00:37:49,520
<i>Go to the center</i>
<i>of gravity's pull...</i>

445
00:37:49,603 --> 00:37:53,190
and find your planet
you will.

446
00:37:57,194 --> 00:38:01,698
Hmm. The data
must have been erased.

447
00:38:01,782 --> 00:38:05,035
But, Master Yoda,
who could empty information
from the archives?

448
00:38:05,118 --> 00:38:06,662
That's impossible,
isn't it?

449
00:38:06,745 --> 00:38:10,123
Dangerous and disturbing
this puzzle is.

450
00:38:10,582 --> 00:38:14,545
Only a Jedi could have
erased those files.

451
00:38:14,628 --> 00:38:18,173
But who and why,
harder to answer.

452
00:38:19,049 --> 00:38:22,719
Meditate on this I will.
Hmm.

453
00:38:46,660 --> 00:38:49,121
I wasn't the youngest queen
ever elected,

454
00:38:49,204 --> 00:38:52,916
but now that I think
back on it, I'm not sure
I was old enough.

455
00:38:52,999 --> 00:38:54,918
I'm not sure
I was ready.

456
00:38:55,002 --> 00:38:58,213
The people you served
thought you did a good job.

457
00:38:58,297 --> 00:39:02,050
I heard they even tried to
amend the constitution
so you could stay in office.

458
00:39:02,134 --> 00:39:04,845
I was relieved
when my two terms were up.

459
00:39:05,679 --> 00:39:08,473
But when the queen
asked me to serve
as senator,

460
00:39:08,557 --> 00:39:10,517
I couldn't refuse her.

461
00:39:10,976 --> 00:39:14,479
I agree with her.
I think the Republic
needs you.

462
00:39:16,398 --> 00:39:18,692
I'm glad that
you chose to serve.

463
00:39:25,490 --> 00:39:27,534
[ Padme ]
If the senate votes
to create an army,

464
00:39:27,618 --> 00:39:31,163
I'm sure it's going
to push us into a civil war.
[ Man ] It's unthinkable.

465
00:39:31,246 --> 00:39:32,789
There hasn't been
a full-scale war

466
00:39:32,873 --> 00:39:34,708
since the formation
of the Republic.

467
00:39:35,042 --> 00:39:37,252
Do you see any way
through negotiations...

468
00:39:37,336 --> 00:39:39,546
to bring the separatists
back into the Republic?

469
00:39:39,630 --> 00:39:41,715
Not if they
feel threatened.

470
00:39:41,798 --> 00:39:43,759
My guess is they'll turn
to the Trade Federations

471
00:39:43,842 --> 00:39:45,093
or the Commerce Guilds
for help.

472
00:39:45,177 --> 00:39:49,640
<i>It's outrageous,</i>
<i>but after four trials</i>
<i>in the Supreme Court,</i>

473
00:39:49,723 --> 00:39:53,644
Nute Gunray
is still the viceroy
of the Trade Federation.

474
00:39:53,727 --> 00:39:57,773
<i>I fear the senate is</i>
<i>powerless to resolve</i>
<i>this crisis.</i>

475
00:39:59,650 --> 00:40:02,110
We must keep our faith
in the Republic.

476
00:40:08,784 --> 00:40:12,955
The day we stop believing
democracy can work
is the day we lose it.

477
00:40:13,038 --> 00:40:15,707
Let's pray
that day never comes.

478
00:40:15,791 --> 00:40:18,544
In the meantime,
we must consider
your own safety.

479
00:40:19,086 --> 00:40:21,672
What is your suggestion,
Master Jedi?

480
00:40:21,755 --> 00:40:23,507
Oh, Anakin's
not a Jedi yet.

481
00:40:23,590 --> 00:40:25,425
He's still
a Padawan learner.
But I was thinking--

482
00:40:25,509 --> 00:40:28,095
Hold on a minute.
Excuse me.

483
00:40:28,428 --> 00:40:30,848
I was thinking I would stay
in the lake country.

484
00:40:30,931 --> 00:40:33,141
There are
some places up there
that are very isolated.

485
00:40:33,225 --> 00:40:36,562
Excuse me.
I'm in charge of
security here, milady.

486
00:40:37,104 --> 00:40:40,190
And this is my home.
I know it very well.
That is why we're here.

487
00:40:40,899 --> 00:40:45,571
<i>I think it would be wise</i>
<i>if you took advantage of</i>
<i>my knowledge in this instance.</i>

488
00:40:46,446 --> 00:40:48,115
Sorry, milady.

489
00:40:51,076 --> 00:40:53,537
[ Queen Jamillia ]
Perfect.
It's settled, then.

490
00:41:07,342 --> 00:41:12,097
There it is, R4,
right where it should be.
Our missing planet Kamino.

491
00:41:12,181 --> 00:41:14,057
[ Whistling, Beeping ]

492
00:41:41,543 --> 00:41:45,047
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

493
00:41:50,636 --> 00:41:52,179
Master Jedi.

494
00:41:53,013 --> 00:41:55,682
The prime minister
is expecting you.

495
00:41:56,808 --> 00:41:59,311
I'm expected?
Of course.

496
00:42:00,103 --> 00:42:02,439
He is anxious to meet you.

497
00:42:02,523 --> 00:42:04,733
<i>After all these years,</i>

498
00:42:04,816 --> 00:42:08,403
we were beginning to think
you weren't coming.

499
00:42:08,487 --> 00:42:10,781
Now, please, this way.

500
00:42:23,377 --> 00:42:25,963
May I present Lama Su,

501
00:42:26,046 --> 00:42:28,215
prime minister of Kamino.

502
00:42:29,842 --> 00:42:32,135
And this is Master Jedi--

503
00:42:32,219 --> 00:42:34,054
Obi-Wan Kenobi.

504
00:42:34,555 --> 00:42:37,558
I trust you're going to
enjoy your stay.

505
00:42:38,767 --> 00:42:40,102
Please.

506
00:42:42,479 --> 00:42:44,690
And now to business.

507
00:42:44,857 --> 00:42:48,861
You will be delighted
to hear that we are
on schedule.

508
00:42:50,028 --> 00:42:51,822
<i>200,000 units are ready,</i>

509
00:42:51,905 --> 00:42:54,366
with a million more
well on the way.

510
00:42:55,409 --> 00:42:57,452
That's good news.

511
00:42:57,536 --> 00:43:00,581
Please tell
your Master Sifo-Dyas...

512
00:43:00,664 --> 00:43:04,084
that his order
will be met on time.

513
00:43:04,251 --> 00:43:06,170
I'm sorry. Master--

514
00:43:06,253 --> 00:43:11,800
Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas
is still a leading member
of the Jedi Council,

515
00:43:11,884 --> 00:43:13,177
is he not?

516
00:43:13,260 --> 00:43:17,097
Master Sifo-Dyas
was killed
almost ten years ago.

517
00:43:17,639 --> 00:43:20,934
Oh, I'm so sorry
to hear that.

518
00:43:21,268 --> 00:43:25,480
But I'm sure he would have
been proud of the army
we've built for him.

519
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:29,026
The army?
Yes.

520
00:43:29,109 --> 00:43:33,989
A clone army, and I must say,
one of the finest
we've ever created.

521
00:43:34,072 --> 00:43:35,866
Tell me, Prime Minister,

522
00:43:35,949 --> 00:43:38,619
when my master first
contacted you
about the army,

523
00:43:38,702 --> 00:43:40,871
did-- did he say
who it was for?

524
00:43:40,954 --> 00:43:42,998
Of course he did.

525
00:43:43,081 --> 00:43:45,751
This army
is for the Republic.

526
00:43:46,668 --> 00:43:50,964
<i>But you must be anxious</i>
<i>to inspect the units</i>
<i>for yourself.</i>

527
00:43:51,757 --> 00:43:53,675
That's why I'm here.

528
00:44:14,655 --> 00:44:16,865
We used to come here
for school retreat.

529
00:44:18,450 --> 00:44:20,661
We would swim to
that island every day.

530
00:44:21,995 --> 00:44:23,789
I love the water.

531
00:44:28,669 --> 00:44:32,714
We used to lie out
on the sand
and let the sun dry us...

532
00:44:32,798 --> 00:44:35,676
and try to guess
the names
of the birds singing.

533
00:44:38,554 --> 00:44:40,347
I don't like sand.

534
00:44:41,473 --> 00:44:45,352
It's coarse and rough
and irritating,

535
00:44:45,435 --> 00:44:47,312
and it gets everywhere.

536
00:44:49,731 --> 00:44:51,358
Not like here.

537
00:44:52,442 --> 00:44:54,528
Here, everything is soft...

538
00:44:56,488 --> 00:44:57,906
and smooth.

539
00:45:35,194 --> 00:45:37,487
No.
[ Gasps ]

540
00:45:37,571 --> 00:45:39,615
I shouldn't have done that.

541
00:45:41,241 --> 00:45:42,743
I'm sorry.

542
00:45:57,007 --> 00:46:00,761
Very impressive.
I'd hoped
you would be pleased.

543
00:46:03,972 --> 00:46:06,517
<i>[ Lama Su ] Clones can</i>
<i>think creatively.</i>

544
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:10,604
<i>You will find that</i>
<i>they are immensely</i>
<i>superior to droids.</i>

545
00:46:14,233 --> 00:46:19,613
We take great pride
in our combat education
and training programs.

546
00:46:19,696 --> 00:46:23,200
This group was created
about five years ago.

547
00:46:23,283 --> 00:46:25,327
<i>[ Obi-Wan ]</i>
<i>You mentioned</i>
<i>growth acceleration.</i>

548
00:46:25,410 --> 00:46:27,371
<i>[ Lama Su ]</i>
<i>Oh, yes, it's essential.</i>

549
00:46:27,454 --> 00:46:30,499
<i>Otherwise,</i>
<i>a mature clone would take</i>
<i>a lifetime to grow.</i>

550
00:46:30,582 --> 00:46:33,210
<i>Now we can do it</i>
<i>in half the time.</i>

551
00:46:33,293 --> 00:46:35,128
<i>[ Obi-Wan ]</i>
<i>I see.</i>

552
00:46:36,004 --> 00:46:37,798
<i>[ Lama Su ]</i>
<i>They are totally obedient,</i>

553
00:46:37,881 --> 00:46:40,634
<i>taking any order</i>
<i>without question.</i>

554
00:46:40,717 --> 00:46:42,886
<i>We modified</i>
<i>their genetic structure...</i>

555
00:46:42,970 --> 00:46:46,306
<i>to make them</i>
<i>less independent</i>
<i>than the original host.</i>

556
00:46:47,057 --> 00:46:48,892
And who was
the original host?

557
00:46:48,976 --> 00:46:51,186
A bounty hunter
called Jango Fett.

558
00:46:52,646 --> 00:46:54,606
And where is
this bounty hunter now?

559
00:46:54,690 --> 00:46:57,150
Oh, we keep him here.

560
00:46:59,444 --> 00:47:02,573
<i>[ Lama Su ]</i>
<i>Apart from his pay,</i>
<i>which is considerable,</i>

561
00:47:02,656 --> 00:47:05,200
Fett demanded
only one thing:

562
00:47:05,284 --> 00:47:07,744
an unaltered clone
for himself.

563
00:47:07,828 --> 00:47:10,289
Curious, isn't it?
"Unaltered"?

564
00:47:10,831 --> 00:47:13,041
[ Lama Su ]
Pure genetic replication.

565
00:47:13,125 --> 00:47:16,336
No tampering
with the structure
to make it more docile...

566
00:47:16,420 --> 00:47:19,047
<i>and no growth acceleration.</i>

567
00:47:19,131 --> 00:47:22,259
I should very much
like to meet
this Jango Fett.

568
00:47:22,342 --> 00:47:25,387
I would be very happy
to arrange it for you.

569
00:47:43,488 --> 00:47:46,408
Magnificent, aren't they?

570
00:47:52,539 --> 00:47:55,042
I don't know.
[ Chuckles ]

571
00:47:55,125 --> 00:47:57,252
Sure you do.
You just don't
want to tell me.

572
00:47:57,336 --> 00:47:59,796
You gonna use one of your
Jedi mind tricks on me?

573
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:02,049
They only work
on the weak-minded.

574
00:48:03,550 --> 00:48:06,637
All right. I was 12.

575
00:48:06,720 --> 00:48:07,763
His name was Palo.

576
00:48:07,846 --> 00:48:09,973
We were both
in the Legislative
Youth Program.

577
00:48:10,057 --> 00:48:13,101
He was a few years
older than I.
Very cute.

578
00:48:13,185 --> 00:48:15,604
Dark, curly hair.
Dreamy eyes.

579
00:48:15,687 --> 00:48:17,856
All right,
I get the picture.

580
00:48:18,190 --> 00:48:19,983
Whatever happened to him?

581
00:48:20,067 --> 00:48:22,986
I went into public service;
he went on to become
an artist.

582
00:48:23,070 --> 00:48:27,366
Maybe he was the smart one.
You really don't like
politicians, do you?

583
00:48:27,449 --> 00:48:29,576
I like two or three,

584
00:48:29,660 --> 00:48:31,870
but I'm not really sure
about one of them.

585
00:48:33,413 --> 00:48:35,040
[ Both Chuckle ]

586
00:48:35,749 --> 00:48:38,126
I don't think
the system works.

587
00:48:38,210 --> 00:48:40,254
How would you
have it work?

588
00:48:41,088 --> 00:48:43,757
We need a system
where the politicians
sit down

589
00:48:43,841 --> 00:48:45,676
and discuss the problem,

590
00:48:45,759 --> 00:48:49,721
agree what's in the best
interest of all the people,
and then do it.

591
00:48:49,805 --> 00:48:51,765
That's exactly what we do.

592
00:48:51,849 --> 00:48:54,059
The trouble is that people
don't always agree.

593
00:48:54,142 --> 00:48:56,061
Well, then
they should be made to.

594
00:48:56,144 --> 00:49:00,107
By whom?
Who's gonna make them? You?
I don't know. Someone.

595
00:49:00,190 --> 00:49:02,526
Of course not me.
But someone.

596
00:49:02,609 --> 00:49:04,444
Someone wise.

597
00:49:04,987 --> 00:49:08,073
Sounds an awful lot
like a dictatorship to me.

598
00:49:09,783 --> 00:49:12,244
Well, if it works.

599
00:49:19,084 --> 00:49:21,044
You're making fun of me.
No.

600
00:49:21,128 --> 00:49:23,881
I'd be much too frightened
to tease a senator.

601
00:49:41,190 --> 00:49:44,234
[ Creature Bellowing ]

602
00:49:44,318 --> 00:49:47,237
<i>[ Anakin ]</i>
<i>Whoa, whoa!</i>
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

603
00:49:48,197 --> 00:49:51,825
[ Bellowing ]
Oh, whoa!
[ Grunting ]

604
00:49:53,744 --> 00:49:55,996
[ Lowing ]
[ Grunts, Groans ]

605
00:50:03,295 --> 00:50:05,339
Ani!
Ani, are you all right?

606
00:50:06,298 --> 00:50:08,800
[ Laughing ]

607
00:50:10,552 --> 00:50:14,097
[ Both Laughing ]

608
00:50:37,996 --> 00:50:39,581
[ Beeping ]

609
00:50:41,708 --> 00:50:44,711
Boba, is your father here?

610
00:50:45,546 --> 00:50:46,713
Yep.

611
00:50:47,339 --> 00:50:48,882
May we see him?

612
00:50:49,591 --> 00:50:50,801
Sure.

613
00:50:53,262 --> 00:50:55,639
Dad, Taun We's here.

614
00:51:04,815 --> 00:51:08,068
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

615
00:51:08,569 --> 00:51:11,405
Jango, welcome back.

616
00:51:11,488 --> 00:51:13,490
<i>Was your trip productive?</i>

617
00:51:13,574 --> 00:51:14,950
Fairly.

618
00:51:15,576 --> 00:51:19,413
This is Jedi Master
Obi-Wan Kenobi.

619
00:51:19,496 --> 00:51:22,499
He's come to check
on our progress.

620
00:51:22,583 --> 00:51:25,627
Your clones
are very impressive.
You must be very proud.

621
00:51:25,711 --> 00:51:28,714
I'm just a simple man
trying to make my way
in the universe.

622
00:51:28,797 --> 00:51:32,509
Ever made your way
as far into the interior
as Coruscant?

623
00:51:32,593 --> 00:51:35,596
Once or twice.
Recently?

624
00:51:37,264 --> 00:51:38,807
Possibly.

625
00:51:39,308 --> 00:51:41,602
Then you must know
Master Sifo-Dyas.

626
00:51:45,981 --> 00:51:48,358
Uh, Boba,
<i>rood eht so-heeck.</i>

627
00:51:49,776 --> 00:51:50,861
Master who?

628
00:51:52,779 --> 00:51:54,740
<i>[ Obi-Wan ]</i>
<i>Sifo-Dyas.</i>

629
00:51:54,823 --> 00:51:57,659
<i>Is he not the Jedi</i>
<i>who hired you for this job?</i>

630
00:52:00,787 --> 00:52:02,456
Never heard of him.

631
00:52:05,459 --> 00:52:06,460
Really?

632
00:52:07,377 --> 00:52:11,590
I was recruited by
a man called Tyranus on
one of the moons of Bogden.

633
00:52:11,673 --> 00:52:13,008
Curious.

634
00:52:17,262 --> 00:52:18,430
Do you like your army?

635
00:52:20,307 --> 00:52:22,267
I look forward
to seeing them in action.

636
00:52:23,519 --> 00:52:26,939
They'll do their job well.
I'll guarantee that.

637
00:52:27,314 --> 00:52:29,650
Thank you for your time,
Jango.

638
00:52:31,151 --> 00:52:33,111
Always a pleasure
to meet a Jedi.

639
00:52:37,658 --> 00:52:40,494
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

640
00:52:52,381 --> 00:52:53,882
What is it, Dad?

641
00:52:55,884 --> 00:52:58,053
Pack your things.
We're leaving.

642
00:53:03,016 --> 00:53:07,312
And when I got to them,
we went into aggressive
negotiations. Thank you.

643
00:53:07,396 --> 00:53:09,481
"Aggressive negotiations"?
What's that?

644
00:53:09,565 --> 00:53:12,609
Uh, well, negotiations
with a lightsaber.

645
00:53:12,693 --> 00:53:14,444
[ Laughing ]
Oh.
[ Laughing ]

646
00:53:25,998 --> 00:53:29,293
If Master Obi-Wan
caught me doing this,
he'd be very grumpy.

647
00:53:58,864 --> 00:54:01,033
From the moment
I met you...

648
00:54:01,825 --> 00:54:04,328
all those years ago,

649
00:54:04,411 --> 00:54:07,581
not a day has gone by
when I haven't
thought of you.

650
00:54:10,125 --> 00:54:12,586
And now that
I'm with you again,

651
00:54:13,170 --> 00:54:15,005
I'm in agony.

652
00:54:18,592 --> 00:54:22,262
The closer I get to you,
the worse it gets.

653
00:54:22,721 --> 00:54:25,182
The thought of
not being with you--

654
00:54:25,933 --> 00:54:27,935
I can't breathe.

655
00:54:32,105 --> 00:54:37,194
I'm haunted by the kiss
that you should
never have given me.

656
00:54:37,277 --> 00:54:39,655
My heart is beating,

657
00:54:39,738 --> 00:54:42,824
hoping that that kiss
will not become a scar.

658
00:54:45,536 --> 00:54:47,663
You are in my very soul,

659
00:54:47,746 --> 00:54:49,498
tormenting me.

660
00:54:52,125 --> 00:54:53,627
What can I do?

661
00:54:53,710 --> 00:54:55,963
I will do anything
that you ask.

662
00:55:06,473 --> 00:55:10,477
If you are suffering
as much as I am,
please, tell me.

663
00:55:12,145 --> 00:55:13,564
I can't.

664
00:55:15,107 --> 00:55:18,235
We can't.
It's... just not possible.

665
00:55:18,485 --> 00:55:21,530
Anything
is possible, Padme.
Listen to me.

666
00:55:21,613 --> 00:55:23,490
No, you listen.

667
00:55:24,157 --> 00:55:27,911
We live in a real world.
Come back to it.

668
00:55:27,995 --> 00:55:31,582
You're studying
to become a Jedi.
I'm-- I'm a senator.

669
00:55:33,834 --> 00:55:36,044
<i>If you follow your thoughts</i>
<i>through to conclusion,</i>

670
00:55:36,128 --> 00:55:39,673
it'll take us
to a place we cannot go,

671
00:55:39,756 --> 00:55:42,092
regardless of the way
we feel about each other.

672
00:55:42,176 --> 00:55:44,261
Then you do
feel something.

673
00:55:44,344 --> 00:55:47,264
I will not let you
give up your future for me.

674
00:55:47,347 --> 00:55:49,683
You are asking me
to be rational.

675
00:55:50,642 --> 00:55:52,978
That is something
I know I cannot do.

676
00:55:53,562 --> 00:55:58,025
Believe me,
I wish that I could just
wish away my feelings,

677
00:55:58,108 --> 00:55:59,735
but I can't.

678
00:56:01,361 --> 00:56:03,572
I will not give in
to this.

679
00:56:10,537 --> 00:56:12,497
Well, you know, it...

680
00:56:12,873 --> 00:56:15,417
wouldn't have to
be that way.

681
00:56:16,543 --> 00:56:18,712
We could keep it a secret.

682
00:56:20,047 --> 00:56:22,132
We'd be living a lie,

683
00:56:22,216 --> 00:56:24,635
one we couldn't keep
even if we wanted to.

684
00:56:25,636 --> 00:56:27,721
I couldn't do that.

685
00:56:28,013 --> 00:56:30,891
Could you, Anakin?
Could you live like that?

686
00:56:32,935 --> 00:56:36,063
No. You're right.

687
00:56:37,314 --> 00:56:39,399
It would destroy us.

688
00:56:47,074 --> 00:56:50,994
Tell your council
that the first battalions
are ready.

689
00:56:51,078 --> 00:56:54,373
And remind them,
if they need more troops,

690
00:56:54,456 --> 00:56:57,626
it will take more time
to grow them.

691
00:56:57,709 --> 00:57:00,379
I won't forget,
and thank you.
<i>Thank you.</i>

692
00:57:17,813 --> 00:57:19,648
R4!
[ Beeping ]

693
00:57:19,731 --> 00:57:23,235
Scramble code five
to Coruscant,
care of the old folks' home!

694
00:57:23,318 --> 00:57:26,071
[ Beeping ]

695
00:57:29,533 --> 00:57:31,285
I have successfully
made contact

696
00:57:31,368 --> 00:57:33,203
with the prime minister
of Kamino.

697
00:57:33,287 --> 00:57:35,706
They are using
a bounty hunter
named Jango Fett

698
00:57:35,789 --> 00:57:37,207
to create a clone army.

699
00:57:37,291 --> 00:57:39,710
I have a strong feeling
that this bounty hunter...

700
00:57:39,793 --> 00:57:41,962
is the assassin
we are looking for.

701
00:57:42,045 --> 00:57:46,216
Do you think these cloners
are involved in the plot to
assassinate Senator Amidala?

702
00:57:46,300 --> 00:57:49,219
No, Master.
There appears to be
no motive.

703
00:57:49,303 --> 00:57:52,222
<i>[ Yoda ]</i>
<i>Do not assume anything,</i>
<i>Obi-Wan.</i>

704
00:57:52,306 --> 00:57:55,225
Clear your mind must be...

705
00:57:55,309 --> 00:57:59,605
if you are to discover
the real villains
behind this plot.

706
00:57:59,688 --> 00:58:01,148
Yes, Master.

707
00:58:01,231 --> 00:58:04,735
They say Master Sifo-Dyas
placed an order
for a clone army...

708
00:58:04,818 --> 00:58:08,405
<i>at the request</i>
<i>of the senate</i>
<i>almost ten years ago.</i>

709
00:58:10,991 --> 00:58:14,119
I was under the impression
he was killed before that.

710
00:58:14,203 --> 00:58:17,706
Did the council
ever authorize the creation
of a clone army?

711
00:58:17,789 --> 00:58:19,583
No. Whoever placed
that order

712
00:58:19,666 --> 00:58:22,211
did not have
the authorization
of the Jedi Council.

713
00:58:22,294 --> 00:58:26,173
Bring him here.
Question him we will.

714
00:58:27,132 --> 00:58:30,177
Yes, Master.
I will report back
when I have him.

715
00:58:31,637 --> 00:58:35,599
Blind we are
if creation of
this clone army...

716
00:58:35,682 --> 00:58:37,684
we could not see.

717
00:58:38,101 --> 00:58:39,520
[ Sighs ]

718
00:58:41,146 --> 00:58:42,981
I think it is time
we informed the senate...

719
00:58:43,065 --> 00:58:45,359
that our ability to use
the Force has diminished.

720
00:58:46,026 --> 00:58:50,447
Only the dark lord
of the Sith
knows of our weakness.

721
00:58:50,531 --> 00:58:52,783
If informed the senate is,

722
00:58:52,866 --> 00:58:55,619
multiply
our adversaries will.

723
00:58:56,870 --> 00:58:59,456
No.
<i>[ Shmi Moaning, Indistinct ]</i>

724
00:58:59,540 --> 00:59:02,000
No.
<i>Anakin! Help me!</i>

725
00:59:02,084 --> 00:59:03,293
Mom, no.

726
00:59:03,377 --> 00:59:06,129
<i>Anakin!</i>
<i>[ Screams ]</i>
Don't.

727
00:59:06,213 --> 00:59:07,422
<i>[ Screaming Stops ]</i>

728
00:59:07,506 --> 00:59:08,674
No.

729
00:59:11,593 --> 00:59:12,803
No.

730
00:59:32,739 --> 00:59:33,991
Don't go.

731
00:59:36,994 --> 00:59:39,079
I don't want to
disturb you.

732
00:59:40,122 --> 00:59:42,207
Your presence is soothing.

733
00:59:45,043 --> 00:59:47,254
You had another nightmare
last night.

734
00:59:48,422 --> 00:59:50,883
Jedi
don't have nightmares.

735
00:59:51,258 --> 00:59:52,759
I heard you.

736
00:59:58,182 --> 01:00:00,017
I saw my mother.

737
01:00:03,270 --> 01:00:05,439
She is suffering,
Padme.

738
01:00:07,858 --> 01:00:10,944
I saw her as clearly
as I see you now.

739
01:00:19,453 --> 01:00:21,330
[ Deep Sigh ]

740
01:00:22,206 --> 01:00:24,208
<i>She is in pain.</i>

741
01:00:25,834 --> 01:00:29,546
I know I'm disobeying
my mandate to protect you,
Senator,

742
01:00:29,630 --> 01:00:31,798
<i>but I have to go.</i>

743
01:00:34,384 --> 01:00:36,345
I have to help her.

744
01:00:38,138 --> 01:00:39,973
I'll go with you.

745
01:00:40,474 --> 01:00:42,935
I'm sorry.
I don't have a choice.

746
01:00:45,729 --> 01:00:49,149
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

747
01:00:53,654 --> 01:00:55,072
Dad, look!

748
01:00:56,406 --> 01:00:57,991
Boba, get on board!

749
01:02:13,567 --> 01:02:16,570
[ Jango Shouts ]
Oh, not good. [ Grunts ]

750
01:04:15,480 --> 01:04:17,191
[ Driver Speaking Huttese ]

751
01:04:26,325 --> 01:04:28,702
Wait right there.
<i>Okey-okey.</i>

752
01:04:30,204 --> 01:04:31,788
<i>Da wanga!</i>

753
01:04:32,539 --> 01:04:33,790
<i>Chut-chut,</i> Watto.

754
01:04:33,957 --> 01:04:35,459
Let me help you with that.

755
01:04:35,626 --> 01:04:37,586
[ Speaking Huttese ]

756
01:04:39,004 --> 01:04:42,341
What? What do you want?

757
01:04:42,799 --> 01:04:44,801
Wait! You’re a Jedi!

758
01:04:45,093 --> 01:04:46,178
[ Grunts ]

759
01:04:46,386 --> 01:04:48,347
Whatever it is...
I didn’t do it.

760
01:04:48,514 --> 01:04:51,725
<i>Ai!</i>
[ Grunts, Sighs ]

761
01:04:54,061 --> 01:04:56,146
I’m looking for Shmi Skywalker.

762
01:04:57,689 --> 01:05:00,067
[ Fly Buzzing ]
[ Speaking Basic ]
Ani?

763
01:05:02,486 --> 01:05:04,279
Little Ani?

764
01:05:07,407 --> 01:05:09,576
Nahhh.

765
01:05:10,911 --> 01:05:14,998
You are Ani! It is you!
[ Laughing ]

766
01:05:15,082 --> 01:05:19,086
You sure sprouted, huh?
<i>Wee-hoo!</i>

767
01:05:19,169 --> 01:05:23,048
A Jedi! Whattaya know!
[ Chuckles ]

768
01:05:23,131 --> 01:05:28,887
Hey... maybe you could
help with some deadbeats
who owe me a lot of money.

769
01:05:28,971 --> 01:05:30,472
My mother.

770
01:05:30,889 --> 01:05:33,225
Oh, yeah. Shmi.

771
01:05:33,308 --> 01:05:37,813
Uh...
she's not mine-a no more-a.
I sold her.

772
01:05:37,896 --> 01:05:40,190
You sold her?
<i>Years ago.</i>

773
01:05:40,274 --> 01:05:44,361
Sorry, Ani, but you know,
business is business, huh?
[ Chuckles ]

774
01:05:44,444 --> 01:05:48,323
Yeah, I sold her
to a moisture farmer
named, uh, Lars.

775
01:05:48,407 --> 01:05:50,367
At least I think
it was Lars.

776
01:05:50,450 --> 01:05:54,037
Believe it or not,
I heard he freed her
and married her!

777
01:05:54,121 --> 01:05:57,624
<i>Can ya beat that, eh?</i>
<i>[ Chuckles ] Yeah.</i>

778
01:05:59,042 --> 01:06:01,003
Do you know
where they are now?

779
01:06:01,086 --> 01:06:03,964
Ooh, long way from here.

780
01:06:04,047 --> 01:06:08,635
Someplace over
on the other side
of Mos Eisley, I think, mmm.

781
01:06:08,969 --> 01:06:10,721
I'd like to know.

782
01:06:12,181 --> 01:06:15,184
Eh, sure. Absolutely!

783
01:06:15,267 --> 01:06:18,061
[ Chuckles ]
Let's go look
at my records, huh?

784
01:06:18,145 --> 01:06:20,814
[ Chuckles ]
Mmm.

785
01:06:45,130 --> 01:06:47,758
[ Beeping ]
<i>Dad!</i>

786
01:06:47,841 --> 01:06:49,760
I think we're being tracked!

787
01:06:49,843 --> 01:06:53,263
<i>[ Jango ]</i>
<i>He must have put</i>
<i>a homing device on our hull.</i>

788
01:06:53,347 --> 01:06:55,724
Hang on, son.
We'll move into
the asteroid field,

789
01:06:55,807 --> 01:06:58,769
and we'll have a couple
of surprises for him.

790
01:06:58,852 --> 01:07:00,187
[ Cackling ]

791
01:07:07,736 --> 01:07:09,488
[ Beeping ]

792
01:07:09,571 --> 01:07:13,116
Seismic charges! Stand by.

793
01:07:20,874 --> 01:07:22,292
[ Beeping ]

794
01:07:38,392 --> 01:07:41,103
He doesn't seem to
take a hint, this guy.

795
01:07:59,746 --> 01:08:00,914
Watch out!

796
01:08:19,391 --> 01:08:23,395
[ Rapid Beeping ]
<i>Get him, Dad! Get him! Fire!</i>

797
01:08:25,314 --> 01:08:27,774
Oh, blast!
This is why I hate flying!

798
01:08:48,045 --> 01:08:51,590
We got him!
We'll just have to
finish him.

799
01:09:17,658 --> 01:09:22,329
R4, prepare to jettison
the spare part canisters.
[ Beeping ]

800
01:09:25,290 --> 01:09:27,751
Fire them now!
[ Beeping ]

801
01:09:39,721 --> 01:09:42,432
Well, we won't be
seeing him again.
[ Chuckles ]

802
01:10:16,967 --> 01:10:21,013
Well, R4, I think
we've waited long enough.
[ Beeping ]

803
01:10:39,573 --> 01:10:43,493
<i>There's an unusual</i>
<i>concentration of Federation</i>
<i>ships over there, R4.</i>

804
01:10:43,577 --> 01:10:45,871
<i>[ R4 Beeps ]</i>

805
01:11:08,393 --> 01:11:10,604
[ Beeping ]

806
01:11:17,778 --> 01:11:20,989
[ R2-D2 Whistles, Beeps ]
[ Padme ]
Stay with the ship, R2.

807
01:11:21,073 --> 01:11:22,783
[ Beeping ]

808
01:11:34,837 --> 01:11:37,214
Oh! Um, uh, hello.

809
01:11:37,297 --> 01:11:40,050
How might I be
of service? I am C--

810
01:11:40,133 --> 01:11:43,887
3PO?
Oh, um--

811
01:11:43,971 --> 01:11:45,597
The maker!

812
01:11:45,681 --> 01:11:49,059
Oh, Master Ani!
I knew you would return.

813
01:11:49,142 --> 01:11:51,979
I knew it!
And Miss Padme. Oh, my.

814
01:11:52,604 --> 01:11:53,981
Hello, 3PO.

815
01:11:54,648 --> 01:11:57,985
Bless my circuits!
I'm so pleased
to see you both.

816
01:11:58,402 --> 01:12:00,070
I've come to see
my mother.

817
01:12:00,153 --> 01:12:04,199
Oh. Um, I think perhaps
we'd better go indoors.

818
01:12:06,827 --> 01:12:11,456
<i>Master Owen,</i>
<i>might I present two</i>
<i>most important visitors.</i>

819
01:12:11,540 --> 01:12:13,625
I'm Anakin Skywalker.

820
01:12:15,169 --> 01:12:18,088
Owen Lars.
Uh, this is
my girlfriend, Beru.

821
01:12:18,172 --> 01:12:21,216
Hello.
I'm Padme.

822
01:12:21,300 --> 01:12:23,886
I guess
I'm your stepbrother.

823
01:12:23,969 --> 01:12:26,847
I had a feeling
you might show up someday.

824
01:12:28,015 --> 01:12:31,310
Is my mother here?
<i>No, she's not.</i>

825
01:12:32,311 --> 01:12:35,397
Cliegg Lars.
Shmi is my wife.

826
01:12:37,107 --> 01:12:40,527
<i>We should go inside.</i>
<i>We have a lot to talk about.</i>

827
01:12:47,951 --> 01:12:51,121
<i>[ Cliegg ]</i>
<i>It was just before dawn.</i>
<i>They came out of nowhere.</i>

828
01:12:51,205 --> 01:12:55,042
<i>A hunting party</i>
<i>of Tusken Raiders.</i>

829
01:12:55,125 --> 01:12:57,961
<i>Your mother had</i>
<i>gone out early,</i>
<i>like she always did,</i>

830
01:12:58,045 --> 01:13:01,840
<i>to pick mushrooms</i>
<i>that grow on the vaporators.</i>

831
01:13:02,090 --> 01:13:05,802
From the tracks,
she was about
halfway home...

832
01:13:05,886 --> 01:13:07,763
when they took her.

833
01:13:09,181 --> 01:13:11,308
[ Sighs ] Those Tuskens
walk like men,

834
01:13:11,391 --> 01:13:16,146
but they're vicious,
mindless monsters.

835
01:13:17,898 --> 01:13:21,068
Thirty of us
went out after her.
Four of us came back.

836
01:13:21,652 --> 01:13:26,240
<i>I'd be out there with them,</i>
<i>but after I lost my leg,</i>

837
01:13:26,323 --> 01:13:31,912
I just couldn't ride anymore
un-until I heal.

838
01:13:31,995 --> 01:13:34,748
<i>I don't want to</i>
<i>give up on her,</i>

839
01:13:34,831 --> 01:13:37,376
<i>but she's been gone</i>
<i>a month.</i>

840
01:13:38,585 --> 01:13:41,630
There's little hope
she's lasted this long.

841
01:13:45,509 --> 01:13:47,427
Where are you going?

842
01:13:48,053 --> 01:13:49,930
To find my mother.

843
01:13:51,098 --> 01:13:54,101
Your mother's dead, son.
Accept it.

844
01:14:16,206 --> 01:14:19,168
<i>You're gonna have to</i>
<i>stay here.</i>

845
01:14:19,251 --> 01:14:22,504
<i>These are</i>
<i>good people, Padme.</i>
<i>You'll be safe.</i>

846
01:14:22,588 --> 01:14:24,131
<i>Anakin--</i>

847
01:14:34,558 --> 01:14:36,476
I won't be long.

848
01:16:01,353 --> 01:16:04,231
<i>[ Machinery Clanging ]</i>

849
01:16:25,752 --> 01:16:27,671
[ Man #1 ]
We must persuade
the Commerce Guild...

850
01:16:27,754 --> 01:16:30,174
and the Corporate Alliance
to sign the treaty.

851
01:16:30,257 --> 01:16:33,677
<i>What about the senator</i>
<i>from Naboo?</i>

852
01:16:33,760 --> 01:16:36,221
<i>Is she dead yet?</i>

853
01:16:36,305 --> 01:16:40,309
I am not signing
your treaty until I have
her head on my desk.

854
01:16:40,392 --> 01:16:42,686
<i>[ Man #1 ]</i>
<i>I am a man of my word,</i>
<i>Viceroy.</i>

855
01:16:42,769 --> 01:16:45,981
<i>[ Alien ]</i>
<i>With these new battle droids</i>
<i>we've built for you,</i>

856
01:16:46,064 --> 01:16:49,359
<i>you'll have the finest army</i>
<i>in the galaxy.</i>

857
01:16:59,953 --> 01:17:01,872
<i>[ Man #1 ]</i>
<i>As I explained</i>
<i>to you earlier,</i>

858
01:17:01,955 --> 01:17:05,417
<i>I am quite convinced</i>
<i>that 10,000 more systems...</i>

859
01:17:05,501 --> 01:17:08,420
will rally to our cause
with your support,
gentlemen.

860
01:17:08,504 --> 01:17:10,631
[ Alien Language ]

861
01:17:10,756 --> 01:17:12,424
What you are proposing could
be construed as treason.

862
01:17:12,633 --> 01:17:14,718
[ Speaking Basic ]
The Techno Union army...

863
01:17:14,801 --> 01:17:18,055
[ Electronic Warbling ]

864
01:17:18,138 --> 01:17:20,724
is at your disposal, Count.

865
01:17:21,350 --> 01:17:25,229
The Banking Clan
will sign your treaty.

866
01:17:25,312 --> 01:17:27,231
<i>[ Man #1 ]</i>
<i>Good. Very good.</i>

867
01:17:28,315 --> 01:17:32,069
Our friends from
the Trade Federation
have pledged their support,

868
01:17:32,152 --> 01:17:34,738
and when their
battle droids are
combined with yours,

869
01:17:34,821 --> 01:17:38,450
we shall have an army
greater than any
in the galaxy.

870
01:17:38,534 --> 01:17:42,246
The Jedi
will be overwhelmed.

871
01:17:42,621 --> 01:17:46,542
The Republic will agree
to any demands we make.

872
01:18:03,016 --> 01:18:05,060
[ Growling ]

873
01:18:07,020 --> 01:18:08,689
[ Snarling ]

874
01:18:15,737 --> 01:18:19,366
<i>[ Growling,</i>
<i>Snarling Continue ]</i>

875
01:18:23,704 --> 01:18:26,206
[ Growling ]

876
01:18:41,346 --> 01:18:42,598
[ Moaning ]

877
01:18:44,308 --> 01:18:45,726
Mom.

878
01:18:47,227 --> 01:18:49,062
Mom? Mom?

879
01:18:51,356 --> 01:18:52,733
Ani?

880
01:18:54,735 --> 01:18:58,739
Ani? Is it you?

881
01:18:59,573 --> 01:19:03,243
I'm here, Mom.
You're safe.

882
01:19:04,411 --> 01:19:05,913
Ani?

883
01:19:07,372 --> 01:19:08,874
Ani?

884
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:12,669
Oh, you look
so handsome.

885
01:19:15,881 --> 01:19:17,925
My son.

886
01:19:18,258 --> 01:19:21,178
Oh, my grown-up son.

887
01:19:22,262 --> 01:19:24,598
I'm so proud of you,
Ani.

888
01:19:25,098 --> 01:19:26,850
I missed you.

889
01:19:29,394 --> 01:19:31,563
Now I am complete.

890
01:19:37,611 --> 01:19:40,614
I love y--

891
01:19:41,782 --> 01:19:45,035
Stay with me, Mom.
Everything--

892
01:19:45,118 --> 01:19:47,287
I love--

893
01:19:48,664 --> 01:19:51,375
I-- I love--

894
01:19:55,087 --> 01:19:57,089
[ Groaning ]

895
01:20:41,091 --> 01:20:42,676
[ Shouting ]

896
01:20:45,846 --> 01:20:46,972
[ Screaming ]

897
01:20:48,348 --> 01:20:52,686
<i>[ Qui-Gon Jinn's Voice ]</i>
<i>Anakin! Anakin! No-o-o!</i>

898
01:21:13,290 --> 01:21:14,374
What is it?

899
01:21:15,375 --> 01:21:19,004
Pain, suffering,

900
01:21:19,421 --> 01:21:21,548
death I feel.

901
01:21:25,928 --> 01:21:29,264
<i>Something terrible</i>
<i>has happened.</i>

902
01:21:31,808 --> 01:21:36,855
Young Skywalker
is in pain.
Terrible pain.

903
01:21:41,735 --> 01:21:45,280
The transmitter is working,
but we're not receiving
a return signal.

904
01:21:45,364 --> 01:21:48,158
Coruscant's too far.
R4, can you boost the power?

905
01:21:48,242 --> 01:21:51,203
[ Beeping ]
We'll have to try
something else.

906
01:21:51,286 --> 01:21:52,704
[ Beeping ]

907
01:21:54,456 --> 01:21:59,002
Maybe we can contact Anakin
on Naboo. It's much closer.

908
01:22:01,255 --> 01:22:03,674
<i>Anakin?</i>
<i>Anakin, do you copy?</i>

909
01:22:03,757 --> 01:22:06,593
<i>This is Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>
<i>Anakin?</i>

910
01:22:06,677 --> 01:22:08,679
<i>He's not on Naboo, R4.</i>

911
01:22:08,762 --> 01:22:10,556
[ Beeping ]

912
01:22:10,639 --> 01:22:13,016
I'm going to try
and widen the range.

913
01:22:16,186 --> 01:22:18,272
I do hope
nothing's happened to him.

914
01:22:25,612 --> 01:22:27,573
<i>That's Anakin's</i>
<i>tracking signal, all right,</i>

915
01:22:27,656 --> 01:22:30,242
but it's coming
from Tatooine.

916
01:22:31,577 --> 01:22:34,204
What in the blazes
is he doing there?

917
01:22:34,288 --> 01:22:36,290
I told him
to stay on Naboo.

918
01:22:36,373 --> 01:22:38,458
[ Beeping ]

919
01:22:39,334 --> 01:22:41,503
We haven't got
much time.

920
01:22:41,587 --> 01:22:43,672
Anakin?
Anakin, do you copy?

921
01:22:43,755 --> 01:22:46,008
This is
Obi-Wan Kenobi.
<i>[ Creature Screeching ]</i>

922
01:22:50,053 --> 01:22:53,682
[ Static,
Obi-Wan's Voice Breaks Up ]

923
01:22:54,099 --> 01:22:57,603
Retransmit this message--
[ Garbled Audio ]

924
01:22:57,686 --> 01:23:00,522
Anakin, do you copy?
Anakin--

925
01:23:00,606 --> 01:23:02,900
My long-range-- [ Static ]
has been knocked out.

926
01:23:02,983 --> 01:23:06,320
Retransmit this message
to Coruscant.
[ Beeping ]

927
01:23:49,696 --> 01:23:51,698
I brought you something.

928
01:23:52,366 --> 01:23:54,201
<i>Are you hungry?</i>

929
01:23:55,744 --> 01:23:57,621
The shifter broke.

930
01:23:59,706 --> 01:24:02,709
Life seems so much simpler
when you're fixing things.

931
01:24:05,003 --> 01:24:08,632
I'm good at fixing things.
Always was.

932
01:24:10,884 --> 01:24:12,719
But I couldn't--

933
01:24:16,849 --> 01:24:18,851
Why'd she have to die?

934
01:24:22,187 --> 01:24:24,356
Why couldn't I save her?

935
01:24:24,439 --> 01:24:26,608
I know I could have!

936
01:24:29,152 --> 01:24:31,989
Sometimes there are things
no one can fix.

937
01:24:33,365 --> 01:24:36,076
You're not
all-powerful, Ani.
Well, I should be!

938
01:24:38,996 --> 01:24:41,081
Someday I will be.

939
01:24:41,164 --> 01:24:44,126
I will be
the most powerful Jedi ever!

940
01:24:45,627 --> 01:24:47,421
I promise you.

941
01:24:48,422 --> 01:24:50,883
I will even learn
to stop people from dying.

942
01:24:51,842 --> 01:24:53,051
Anakin.

943
01:24:54,428 --> 01:24:56,930
It's all Obi-Wan's fault!

944
01:24:57,181 --> 01:25:00,267
He's jealous!
He's holding me back!

945
01:25:00,350 --> 01:25:03,770
[ Object Clattering ]
[ Sniffling ]

946
01:25:04,897 --> 01:25:06,982
What's wrong, Ani?

947
01:25:12,446 --> 01:25:13,947
I--

948
01:25:17,784 --> 01:25:19,578
I killed them.

949
01:25:21,455 --> 01:25:23,415
I killed them all.

950
01:25:25,250 --> 01:25:26,835
They're dead.

951
01:25:27,461 --> 01:25:29,630
Every single one of them.

952
01:25:31,507 --> 01:25:33,717
And not just the men,

953
01:25:35,469 --> 01:25:37,679
but the women...

954
01:25:37,763 --> 01:25:39,681
and the children too.

955
01:25:41,141 --> 01:25:42,768
<i>They're like animals,</i>

956
01:25:42,851 --> 01:25:45,187
<i>and I slaughtered them</i>
<i>like animals!</i>

957
01:25:46,730 --> 01:25:48,357
I hate them!

958
01:25:58,158 --> 01:26:00,285
<i>[ Anakin Exhales ]</i>

959
01:26:06,375 --> 01:26:08,544
To be angry
is to be human.

960
01:26:09,044 --> 01:26:10,838
I'm a Jedi.

961
01:26:11,505 --> 01:26:13,590
I know
I'm better than this.

962
01:26:27,354 --> 01:26:32,234
<i>[ Cliegg ]</i>
<i>I know wherever you are</i>
<i>it's become a better place.</i>

963
01:26:32,317 --> 01:26:37,322
You were
the most loving partner
a man could ever have.

964
01:26:40,117 --> 01:26:42,411
Good-bye, my darling wife.

965
01:26:46,206 --> 01:26:48,041
And thank you.

966
01:27:15,277 --> 01:27:17,905
I wasn't strong enough
to save you, Mom.

967
01:27:20,699 --> 01:27:22,284
<i>I wasn't strong enough.</i>

968
01:27:26,580 --> 01:27:30,250
But I promise
I won't fail again.

969
01:27:40,886 --> 01:27:43,096
I miss you...

970
01:27:44,515 --> 01:27:46,433
so much.

971
01:27:50,562 --> 01:27:52,314
[ Beeping ]

972
01:27:53,607 --> 01:27:56,068
R2?
What are you doing here?

973
01:27:56,151 --> 01:27:57,945
[ Beeping ]

974
01:27:58,779 --> 01:28:03,200
It seems that he is
carrying a message from
an Obi-Wan Kenobi.

975
01:28:03,283 --> 01:28:06,662
Hmm. Master Ani,
does that name
mean anything to you?

976
01:28:06,745 --> 01:28:08,038
[ Beeping ]

977
01:28:09,289 --> 01:28:11,917
Anakin,
my long-range transmitter
has been knocked out.

978
01:28:12,000 --> 01:28:14,378
Retransmit this message
to Coruscant.

979
01:28:18,632 --> 01:28:21,009
I have tracked
the bounty hunter,
Jango Fett,

980
01:28:21,093 --> 01:28:23,303
to the droid foundries
on Geonosis.

981
01:28:23,387 --> 01:28:26,807
The Trade Federation
is to take delivery
of a droid army here,

982
01:28:26,890 --> 01:28:29,226
and it is clear
that Viceroy Gunray...

983
01:28:29,309 --> 01:28:32,771
is behind
the assassination attempts
on Senator Amidala.

984
01:28:32,855 --> 01:28:34,940
The Commerce Guilds and
the Corporate Alliance...

985
01:28:35,023 --> 01:28:38,777
have both pledged their
armies to Count Dooku
and are forming a--

986
01:28:38,861 --> 01:28:40,988
Wait. Wait.

987
01:28:41,071 --> 01:28:45,033
<i>[ Lightsaber Whooshing ]</i>
<i>[ Obi-Wan Grunting ]</i>

988
01:28:51,874 --> 01:28:56,420
More happening on Geonosis,
I feel, than has
been revealed.

989
01:28:56,587 --> 01:28:58,005
I agree.

990
01:28:58,672 --> 01:29:01,925
Anakin, we will deal
with Count Dooku.

991
01:29:02,009 --> 01:29:05,721
The most important thing
for you is to stay
where you are.

992
01:29:05,804 --> 01:29:08,473
Protect the senator
at all costs.

993
01:29:08,557 --> 01:29:11,226
That is
your first priority.

994
01:29:12,477 --> 01:29:14,396
Understood, Master.

995
01:29:14,479 --> 01:29:16,023
They'll never get there
in time to save him.

996
01:29:16,106 --> 01:29:19,318
They have to come
halfway across the galaxy.
Look.

997
01:29:21,904 --> 01:29:24,072
Geonosis is less
than a parsec away.

998
01:29:24,698 --> 01:29:26,700
If he's still alive.

999
01:29:27,951 --> 01:29:30,621
Ani, are you just
gonna sit here
and let him die?

1000
01:29:30,704 --> 01:29:33,373
He's your friend,
your mentor. He's--
He's like my father!

1001
01:29:34,541 --> 01:29:38,337
But you heard Master Windu.
He gave me strict orders
to stay here!

1002
01:29:38,587 --> 01:29:41,673
He gave you strict orders
to protect me,

1003
01:29:41,757 --> 01:29:44,092
and I'm going
to help Obi-Wan.

1004
01:29:45,135 --> 01:29:48,180
If you plan to protect me,
you'll just have to
come along.

1005
01:29:48,263 --> 01:29:49,973
<i>[ Engines Power Up ]</i>

1006
01:29:52,684 --> 01:29:56,230
I'm not worried, R2.
It's just I've never flown
before.

1007
01:30:06,281 --> 01:30:07,950
The Commerce Guilds
are preparing for war.

1008
01:30:08,033 --> 01:30:09,326
There can be
no doubt of that.

1009
01:30:09,409 --> 01:30:11,537
[ Palpatine ]
Count Dooku must have made
a treaty with them.

1010
01:30:11,620 --> 01:30:14,831
[ Alien Language ]

1011
01:30:15,040 --> 01:30:16,291
The debate is over!

1012
01:30:16,750 --> 01:30:17,876
Now we need that clone army.

1013
01:30:18,252 --> 01:30:21,046
[ Speaking Basic ]
Unfortunately,
the debate is not over.

1014
01:30:21,129 --> 01:30:23,674
The senate will never
approve the use of clones

1015
01:30:23,757 --> 01:30:25,509
before the separatists
attack.

1016
01:30:25,592 --> 01:30:27,010
This is a crisis.

1017
01:30:27,094 --> 01:30:30,722
The senate must vote
the chancellor
emergency powers.

1018
01:30:30,806 --> 01:30:34,101
<i>He can then approve</i>
<i>the creation of an army.</i>

1019
01:30:34,184 --> 01:30:39,106
But what senator would
have the courage to propose
such a radical amendment?

1020
01:30:39,189 --> 01:30:43,443
If only...
Senator Amidala were here.

1021
01:30:44,987 --> 01:30:46,363
Mm.

1022
01:30:52,452 --> 01:30:54,454
[ Screeching ]

1023
01:30:57,249 --> 01:30:59,835
[ Grumbling ]

1024
01:31:04,464 --> 01:31:05,799
Traitor.

1025
01:31:06,842 --> 01:31:10,304
Oh, no, my friend.
This is a mistake,
a terrible mistake.

1026
01:31:10,387 --> 01:31:12,389
They have gone too far.
This is madness.

1027
01:31:12,472 --> 01:31:15,100
I thought you
were the leader here,
Dooku.

1028
01:31:15,184 --> 01:31:17,853
This had nothing
to do with me,
I assure you.

1029
01:31:17,936 --> 01:31:21,231
<i>I will petition immediately</i>
<i>to have you set free.</i>

1030
01:31:21,315 --> 01:31:25,110
Well, I hope
it doesn't take too long.
I have work to do.

1031
01:31:25,194 --> 01:31:29,031
May I ask
why a Jedi knight...

1032
01:31:29,114 --> 01:31:31,658
is all the way
out here on Geonosis?

1033
01:31:31,742 --> 01:31:34,578
I've been tracking
a bounty hunter
named Jango Fett.

1034
01:31:34,661 --> 01:31:36,163
Do you know him?

1035
01:31:36,246 --> 01:31:39,041
There are no
bounty hunters here
that I am aware of.

1036
01:31:39,124 --> 01:31:41,084
The Geonosians
don't trust them.

1037
01:31:41,168 --> 01:31:44,338
Who can blame them?
But he is here,
I can assure you.

1038
01:31:45,214 --> 01:31:50,219
It's a great pity that
our paths have never
crossed before, Obi-Wan.

1039
01:31:50,302 --> 01:31:52,846
Qui-Gon always spoke
very highly of you.

1040
01:31:57,476 --> 01:31:59,728
I wish he were still alive.

1041
01:32:01,063 --> 01:32:03,815
I could use his help
right now.

1042
01:32:04,608 --> 01:32:06,860
Qui-Gon Jinn would
never join you.

1043
01:32:08,820 --> 01:32:11,782
Don't be so sure,
my young Jedi.

1044
01:32:11,865 --> 01:32:14,451
You forget that he was
once my apprentice,

1045
01:32:14,535 --> 01:32:16,620
just as you
were once his.

1046
01:32:17,371 --> 01:32:19,540
He knew all about
the corruption
in the senate,

1047
01:32:19,623 --> 01:32:21,291
but he would never have
gone along with it

1048
01:32:21,375 --> 01:32:22,960
if he had learned
the truth as I have.

1049
01:32:23,043 --> 01:32:25,712
The truth?
The truth.

1050
01:32:32,052 --> 01:32:33,846
What if I told you
that the Republic...

1051
01:32:33,929 --> 01:32:37,266
was now under the control
of the dark lord
of the Sith?

1052
01:32:37,349 --> 01:32:40,727
No, that's not possible.
The Jedi would be
aware of it.

1053
01:32:40,811 --> 01:32:45,691
The dark side of the Force
has clouded their vision,
my friend.

1054
01:32:46,066 --> 01:32:48,652
Hundreds of senators
are now under
the influence...

1055
01:32:48,735 --> 01:32:53,407
of a Sith lord
called Darth Sidious.

1056
01:32:54,241 --> 01:32:56,076
I don't believe you.

1057
01:32:56,159 --> 01:32:58,412
<i>The viceroy of</i>
<i>the Trade Federation...</i>

1058
01:32:58,495 --> 01:33:02,499
<i>was once in league</i>
<i>with this Darth Sidious,</i>

1059
01:33:02,875 --> 01:33:06,712
but he was betrayed
ten years ago
by the dark lord.

1060
01:33:06,795 --> 01:33:09,965
He came to me for help.
He told me everything.

1061
01:33:11,675 --> 01:33:14,094
You must join me,
Obi-Wan,

1062
01:33:15,012 --> 01:33:18,932
and together
we will destroy the Sith!

1063
01:33:20,767 --> 01:33:23,270
I will never join you,
Dooku.

1064
01:33:32,487 --> 01:33:35,616
It may be difficult
to secure your release.

1065
01:33:43,123 --> 01:33:46,210
<i>[ Jar Jar ] It's-a clear</i>
<i>desa separatists</i>
<i>made a pact...</i>

1066
01:33:46,293 --> 01:33:49,004
<i>wesa desa</i>
<i>Federation du Trade.</i>

1067
01:33:49,087 --> 01:33:53,300
<i>Senators,</i>
<i>"dellow felagates":</i>

1068
01:33:53,383 --> 01:33:57,638
<i>In response to</i>
<i>this direct threat</i>
<i>to the Republic,</i>

1069
01:33:57,721 --> 01:34:01,433
mesa propose
that the senate...

1070
01:34:01,517 --> 01:34:04,978
give immediately
emergency powers...

1071
01:34:05,062 --> 01:34:07,606
to the supreme chancellor.

1072
01:34:07,689 --> 01:34:10,067
[ Shouts Of Approval ]

1073
01:34:10,150 --> 01:34:14,154
Palpatine! Palpatine!
Palpatine!

1074
01:34:14,238 --> 01:34:17,115
[ Shouting In Alien Language ]

1075
01:34:17,199 --> 01:34:20,577
<i>[ Senate Chairman ]</i>
<i>Order! We shall have order!</i>

1076
01:34:21,995 --> 01:34:25,332
It is
with great reluctance...

1077
01:34:25,415 --> 01:34:27,668
that I have agreed
to this calling.

1078
01:34:28,794 --> 01:34:33,715
I love democracy.
I love the Republic.
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

1079
01:34:34,007 --> 01:34:36,134
<i>The power you give me...</i>

1080
01:34:36,218 --> 01:34:40,264
I will lay down when
this crisis has abated.

1081
01:34:40,347 --> 01:34:44,017
[ Cheering, Applause ]

1082
01:34:45,602 --> 01:34:50,107
And as my first act
with this new authority,

1083
01:34:50,190 --> 01:34:54,611
I will create
a grand army
of the Republic...

1084
01:34:54,695 --> 01:34:58,657
to counter
the increasing threats
of the separatists.

1085
01:34:59,616 --> 01:35:01,535
It is done, then.

1086
01:35:01,869 --> 01:35:03,245
Hmm.

1087
01:35:06,707 --> 01:35:10,669
I will take what Jedi
we have left and go to
Geonosis and help Obi-Wan.

1088
01:35:10,752 --> 01:35:15,507
Visit I will
the cloners on Kamino, hmm,

1089
01:35:15,591 --> 01:35:19,553
and see this army
they have created
for the Republic.

1090
01:35:39,948 --> 01:35:42,075
See those columns of steam
straight ahead?

1091
01:35:42,159 --> 01:35:44,244
They're exhaust vents
of some type.

1092
01:35:44,828 --> 01:35:46,205
That'll do.

1093
01:35:56,215 --> 01:35:59,468
Look, whatever
happens out there,
follow my lead.

1094
01:35:59,551 --> 01:36:01,637
I'm not interested
in getting into a war here.

1095
01:36:01,720 --> 01:36:03,013
As a member of the senate,

1096
01:36:03,096 --> 01:36:05,933
maybe I can find
a diplomatic solution
to this mess.

1097
01:36:06,725 --> 01:36:11,104
Don't worry. I've given up
trying to argue with you.

1098
01:36:12,940 --> 01:36:15,901
<i>[ Whistling, Beeping ]</i>

1099
01:36:16,276 --> 01:36:19,488
My obtuse little friend,
if they had needed our help,

1100
01:36:19,571 --> 01:36:21,490
they would have
asked for it, hmm?

1101
01:36:21,573 --> 01:36:24,368
You obviously have
a great deal to learn
about human behavior.

1102
01:36:24,451 --> 01:36:25,827
[ Beeping ]

1103
01:36:49,226 --> 01:36:51,728
[ Beeping ]
For a mechanic,

1104
01:36:51,812 --> 01:36:53,814
you seem to do an excessive
amount of thinking.

1105
01:36:53,897 --> 01:36:58,485
[ Beeping ]
I am programmed
to understand humans!

1106
01:36:58,569 --> 01:37:00,779
[ Beeping ]

1107
01:37:02,030 --> 01:37:03,907
"What does that mean?" Oh!

1108
01:37:03,991 --> 01:37:06,785
That means
I am in charge here!
<i>[ Raspberries ]</i>

1109
01:37:06,869 --> 01:37:09,913
Where are you going now?
You don't know
what's out there.

1110
01:37:09,997 --> 01:37:13,333
Have you no sense at all?
Oh! Idiot!

1111
01:37:16,295 --> 01:37:18,839
Please wait.
[ Beeping ]

1112
01:37:18,922 --> 01:37:20,883
Do you know
where you're going?

1113
01:37:33,395 --> 01:37:34,688
Wait.

1114
01:37:37,357 --> 01:37:38,901
[ Squawking ]

1115
01:37:43,280 --> 01:37:45,532
Oh, my-- Oh, oh, oh!

1116
01:37:55,709 --> 01:37:57,711
[ Screaming ]
<i>Padme!</i>

1117
01:38:21,652 --> 01:38:23,695
Ah!
[ Grunts ]

1118
01:38:50,597 --> 01:38:54,309
Oh, my goodness!
Shut me down!

1119
01:38:55,143 --> 01:38:57,396
<i>Machines making machines.</i>

1120
01:38:57,479 --> 01:39:00,274
Huh! How perverse.
[ Grunts ] Oh!

1121
01:39:00,357 --> 01:39:03,944
Calm down, R2.
I almost fell.

1122
01:39:04,027 --> 01:39:06,113
You'll get your chance--

1123
01:39:07,865 --> 01:39:10,868
Oh! I'm scrap.
[ Grunting ]

1124
01:39:10,951 --> 01:39:13,787
It's a nightmare!

1125
01:39:15,080 --> 01:39:17,124
Oh, I want to go home!
Ahh!

1126
01:39:18,333 --> 01:39:20,502
Oh, what did I do
to deserve this?

1127
01:39:20,794 --> 01:39:22,004
[ Beeping ]

1128
01:39:26,133 --> 01:39:29,052
[ Whistling ]

1129
01:39:39,771 --> 01:39:42,816
[ Padme Grunting ]
[ Geonosian Screeching ]

1130
01:39:43,442 --> 01:39:44,651
Ahhh!

1131
01:39:57,706 --> 01:40:02,628
[ Whistling ]
Hmm. I wonder what happened
to poor little R2.

1132
01:40:02,711 --> 01:40:05,255
He's always getting himself
into trouble. Oops.

1133
01:40:06,465 --> 01:40:07,841
Oh, no!

1134
01:40:17,726 --> 01:40:19,019
Uh-oh.

1135
01:40:20,187 --> 01:40:21,313
Oh!

1136
01:40:22,648 --> 01:40:24,608
Oh, I'm so confused.

1137
01:42:19,431 --> 01:42:21,767
Oh, not again.

1138
01:42:22,809 --> 01:42:24,853
Obi-Wan's gonna kill me.

1139
01:42:33,820 --> 01:42:36,990
Don't move, Jedi!
Take him away.

1140
01:42:56,218 --> 01:42:57,803
Don't be afraid.

1141
01:42:59,596 --> 01:43:01,515
I'm not afraid to die.

1142
01:43:06,228 --> 01:43:10,524
I've been dying a little bit
each day since you came back
into my life.

1143
01:43:11,817 --> 01:43:14,152
What are you
talking about?

1144
01:43:15,571 --> 01:43:17,364
I love you.

1145
01:43:21,702 --> 01:43:23,537
You love me?

1146
01:43:28,041 --> 01:43:31,503
I thought that
we had decided
not to fall in love,

1147
01:43:33,463 --> 01:43:36,884
that we would be forced
to live a lie...

1148
01:43:36,967 --> 01:43:40,053
and that it would
destroy our lives.

1149
01:43:40,721 --> 01:43:43,891
I think our lives are about
to be destroyed anyway.

1150
01:43:48,061 --> 01:43:49,646
I truly,

1151
01:43:51,064 --> 01:43:53,859
deeply love you,

1152
01:43:54,735 --> 01:43:57,487
and before we die,
I want you to know.

1153
01:44:04,786 --> 01:44:06,413
Eeyah!

1154
01:44:13,879 --> 01:44:16,924
[ Loud Cheering ]

1155
01:44:35,025 --> 01:44:37,027
[ Cheering ]

1156
01:44:54,753 --> 01:44:57,214
I was beginning to wonder
if you'd got my message.

1157
01:44:57,297 --> 01:45:00,551
I retransmitted it
just as you had requested,
Master.

1158
01:45:02,636 --> 01:45:04,596
Then we decided to
come and rescue you.

1159
01:45:05,931 --> 01:45:07,182
Good job.

1160
01:45:13,230 --> 01:45:15,691
[ Cheering ]

1161
01:45:15,858 --> 01:45:19,069
Settle down. Settle down.

1162
01:45:19,194 --> 01:45:21,780
[ Speaking Geonosian ]

1163
01:45:22,656 --> 01:45:24,533
[ Cheering Subsides ]

1164
01:45:27,160 --> 01:45:29,663
Let the executions begin.

1165
01:45:30,289 --> 01:45:32,749
[ Cheering ]

1166
01:45:42,843 --> 01:45:44,678
[ Roaring ]

1167
01:45:47,723 --> 01:45:49,516
[ Screeching ]

1168
01:45:52,144 --> 01:45:53,395
[ Roaring ]

1169
01:45:55,063 --> 01:45:56,356
[ Roaring ]

1170
01:46:03,030 --> 01:46:05,741
I've got a bad feeling
about this.

1171
01:46:06,700 --> 01:46:08,368
[ Shouting ]
[ Bellowing ]

1172
01:46:09,870 --> 01:46:11,246
[ Creatures Roaring ]

1173
01:46:12,497 --> 01:46:14,750
<i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

1174
01:46:22,549 --> 01:46:24,384
[ Snarling ]

1175
01:46:31,475 --> 01:46:33,977
Just relax. Concentrate.
What about Padme?

1176
01:46:34,061 --> 01:46:36,230
She seems to be
on top of things.

1177
01:46:38,690 --> 01:46:40,234
[ Roaring ]

1178
01:46:55,207 --> 01:46:56,416
[ Bellowing ]

1179
01:46:59,962 --> 01:47:01,839
[ Roaring ]

1180
01:47:07,010 --> 01:47:09,847
[ Screaming ]
[ Snarling ]

1181
01:47:10,973 --> 01:47:12,641
[ Chuckling ]

1182
01:47:29,867 --> 01:47:31,285
[ Yelling ]

1183
01:47:37,082 --> 01:47:38,500
[ Creature Yelps ]

1184
01:47:39,209 --> 01:47:43,005
She can't do that!
Shoot her or-- or something!

1185
01:47:46,842 --> 01:47:52,014
[ Whimpering, Snarling ]

1186
01:48:07,988 --> 01:48:10,490
[ Shrieking ]
[ Roaring ]

1187
01:48:16,121 --> 01:48:18,373
[ Hissing, Growling ]

1188
01:48:26,256 --> 01:48:27,841
[ Screaming ]

1189
01:48:28,133 --> 01:48:29,843
[ Subdued Growling ]

1190
01:48:36,350 --> 01:48:40,187
Whoa! Yah!
[ Growling, Roaring ]

1191
01:48:41,855 --> 01:48:44,066
Hyah! Hyah!

1192
01:48:44,149 --> 01:48:46,026
[ Cheering ]

1193
01:48:58,205 --> 01:49:00,082
[ Snarling ]
<i>[ Bellowing ]</i>

1194
01:49:02,209 --> 01:49:03,210
Jump!

1195
01:49:08,841 --> 01:49:10,384
Hyah! Hyah!

1196
01:49:13,136 --> 01:49:15,722
<i>[ Shrieking ]</i>

1197
01:49:20,227 --> 01:49:22,271
[ Cheering ]
[ Shouting ]

1198
01:49:27,484 --> 01:49:32,573
This isn't how
it's supposed to be!
Jango! Finish her off!

1199
01:49:32,781 --> 01:49:36,159
Patience, Viceroy, patience.
She will die.

1200
01:50:06,690 --> 01:50:10,569
Master Windu,
how pleasant of you
to join us.

1201
01:50:10,986 --> 01:50:12,571
This party's over.

1202
01:50:26,627 --> 01:50:31,006
Brave but, uh, foolish,
my old Jedi friend.

1203
01:50:31,632 --> 01:50:35,594
You're impossibly outnumbered.
[ Scoffs ]
I don't think so.

1204
01:50:35,677 --> 01:50:38,347
We'll see.
[ Heavy Footsteps
Approaching ]

1205
01:51:14,967 --> 01:51:18,387
[ Synthesized Voice ]
My legs aren't moving.
I must need maintenance.

1206
01:51:57,968 --> 01:52:00,637
[ C-3PO ]
What's all this noise?
A-A battle!

1207
01:52:00,721 --> 01:52:02,931
Oh, there's been
some terrible mistake!

1208
01:52:03,015 --> 01:52:05,851
I'm programmed for etiquette,
not destruction!

1209
01:52:37,132 --> 01:52:40,260
[ Roaring ]
[ Obi-Wan Grunts ]

1210
01:52:50,479 --> 01:52:52,981
[ Roaring ]

1211
01:52:53,065 --> 01:52:57,110
[ Groaning, Yelling ]

1212
01:53:08,622 --> 01:53:10,916
[ Yowling ]

1213
01:53:33,355 --> 01:53:37,109
Die, Jedi dogs!
Oh! What did I say?

1214
01:53:41,154 --> 01:53:42,406
Hah!

1215
01:53:46,159 --> 01:53:49,454
Oh, dear.
I'm terribly sorry
about all this.

1216
01:53:50,664 --> 01:53:51,832
Ohh!

1217
01:53:55,169 --> 01:53:57,963
Excuse me. I'm trapped.
I can't get up.

1218
01:54:11,852 --> 01:54:13,604
<i>You call this</i>
<i>a diplomatic solution?</i>

1219
01:54:13,687 --> 01:54:16,064
No, I call it
aggressive negotiations.

1220
01:54:21,069 --> 01:54:23,071
Uh-oh.
Roger, roger.

1221
01:54:23,697 --> 01:54:27,201
[ Growling, Screeching ]

1222
01:54:36,585 --> 01:54:38,921
[ Creature Shrieking ]

1223
01:54:40,631 --> 01:54:43,509
[ Beeping ]
R2, what are you
doing here?

1224
01:54:43,592 --> 01:54:45,219
[ Beeping ]

1225
01:54:46,720 --> 01:54:49,264
What<i> are</i> you doing?
Oh, stop that!

1226
01:54:49,348 --> 01:54:51,725
You're going to
strain something.
My neck!

1227
01:54:54,394 --> 01:54:58,065
Now where are you taking me?
Oh, this is such a drag.
[ Beeping ]

1228
01:55:02,236 --> 01:55:05,072
[ C-3PO ]
Oh, I'm quite
beside myself.

1229
01:55:13,830 --> 01:55:16,792
R2, please be careful!
You're singeing
my circuits!

1230
01:55:16,875 --> 01:55:20,838
[ Beeping ]
Yes, but is my head
on straight?

1231
01:55:43,652 --> 01:55:47,781
<i>[ Dooku ]</i>
<i>Master Windu,</i>
<i>you have fought gallantly,</i>

1232
01:55:48,824 --> 01:55:52,995
<i>worthy of recognition</i>
<i>in the archives</i>
<i>of the Jedi order.</i>

1233
01:55:55,038 --> 01:55:58,166
<i>Now it is finished.</i>

1234
01:55:59,793 --> 01:56:04,423
Surrender, and your lives
will be spared.

1235
01:56:05,048 --> 01:56:08,510
We will not be hostages
to be bartered, Dooku!

1236
01:56:09,052 --> 01:56:13,056
<i>Then, I'm sorry,</i>
<i>old friend.</i>

1237
01:56:24,693 --> 01:56:25,986
Look!

1238
01:56:36,830 --> 01:56:40,959
Around the survivors
a perimeter create.

1239
01:57:32,928 --> 01:57:35,222
[ Beeping, Chirping ]

1240
01:57:36,557 --> 01:57:40,686
Oh, I've had
the most peculiar dream.

1241
01:57:51,405 --> 01:57:53,323
If Dooku escapes,

1242
01:57:53,407 --> 01:57:56,076
rally more systems
to his cause he will.

1243
01:58:01,874 --> 01:58:03,417
Hold on!

1244
01:58:08,130 --> 01:58:10,090
Aim right above
the fuel cells!

1245
01:58:16,889 --> 01:58:19,266
Good call,
my young Padawan.

1246
01:58:32,696 --> 01:58:35,240
[ Viceroy Gunray ]
The Jedi have amassed
a huge army.

1247
01:58:35,324 --> 01:58:37,659
That doesn't seem possible.

1248
01:58:37,743 --> 01:58:40,370
How could the Jedi
come up with an army
so quickly?

1249
01:58:40,454 --> 01:58:44,208
We must send
all available droids
into battle.

1250
01:58:44,291 --> 01:58:45,792
There are too many.

1251
01:58:46,460 --> 01:58:48,962
[ Speaking Geonosian ]

1252
01:58:49,296 --> 01:58:51,882
Our communications have been
jammed.

1253
01:58:57,304 --> 01:59:01,975
Pilot,
land in that assembly area!
Yes, sir.

1254
01:59:10,067 --> 01:59:13,987
Sir, I have
five special commando units
awaiting your orders, sir.

1255
01:59:15,322 --> 01:59:18,492
To the forward
command center
take me.

1256
01:59:41,723 --> 01:59:44,518
Attack those Federation
starships! Quickly!

1257
01:59:55,487 --> 01:59:59,283
Master Yoda,
all forward positions
are advancing.

1258
01:59:59,658 --> 02:00:03,370
Very good. Very good.

1259
02:00:31,440 --> 02:00:33,859
[ Viceroy Gunray ]
This is not
looking good at all!

1260
02:00:35,277 --> 02:00:38,572
We must get the starships
back into space.

1261
02:00:38,780 --> 02:00:41,283
We have to order a retreat.

1262
02:00:41,575 --> 02:00:45,329
[ Speaking Geonosian ]

1263
02:00:45,412 --> 02:00:47,831
My master will never
allow the Republic...

1264
02:00:47,915 --> 02:00:50,042
to get away
with this treachery.

1265
02:00:50,292 --> 02:00:53,837
I’m sending my warriors to
hide in the catacombs.

1266
02:00:54,296 --> 02:00:58,675
The Jedi must not find our
designs for the ultimate weapon.

1267
02:01:00,260 --> 02:01:05,474
If they find out what we are
planning to build, we’re doomed.

1268
02:01:06,725 --> 02:01:08,602
[ Geonosian ]

1269
02:01:08,685 --> 02:01:11,104
I will take the designs
with me to Coruscant.

1270
02:01:11,939 --> 02:01:15,108
They will be
much safer there
with my master.

1271
02:01:33,252 --> 02:01:36,171
<i>[ Alarm Blaring ]</i>

1272
02:02:09,496 --> 02:02:14,168
Concentrate all your fire
on the nearest starship.

1273
02:02:14,626 --> 02:02:15,961
Yes, sir.

1274
02:02:16,670 --> 02:02:19,631
Move all quadrants
to sector 5-1-5.

1275
02:03:00,005 --> 02:03:01,298
Look over there!

1276
02:03:04,718 --> 02:03:07,137
It's Dooku!
Shoot him down!

1277
02:03:07,429 --> 02:03:09,139
We're out of rockets, sir.

1278
02:03:09,223 --> 02:03:12,142
Follow him!
We're gonna need some help!

1279
02:03:12,226 --> 02:03:16,146
There isn't time!
Anakin and I
can handle this!

1280
02:03:18,065 --> 02:03:19,858
[ Beeping ]

1281
02:03:33,455 --> 02:03:36,750
[ Padme Yells ]
<i>[ Anakin ] Padme!</i>

1282
02:03:39,920 --> 02:03:42,339
Put the ship down!
Anakin!

1283
02:03:42,422 --> 02:03:44,424
Don't let
your personal feelings
get in the way!

1284
02:03:44,967 --> 02:03:46,260
Follow that speeder!

1285
02:03:52,307 --> 02:03:54,560
Lower the ship!
I can't take Dooku alone!

1286
02:03:54,643 --> 02:03:55,686
I need you!

1287
02:03:55,769 --> 02:03:58,230
If we catch him,
we can end this war
right now!

1288
02:03:58,313 --> 02:04:01,358
We have a job to do!
I don't care!
Put the ship down!

1289
02:04:01,441 --> 02:04:03,735
You will be expelled
from the Jedi order!

1290
02:04:03,819 --> 02:04:06,947
I can't leave her!
Come to your senses!

1291
02:04:07,030 --> 02:04:09,825
What do you think
Padme would do
were she in your position?

1292
02:04:14,288 --> 02:04:16,290
She would do her duty.

1293
02:04:19,960 --> 02:04:21,420
Hmm.

1294
02:04:25,424 --> 02:04:27,384
The droid army
is in full retreat.

1295
02:04:27,467 --> 02:04:30,721
Well done, Commander.
Bring me a ship.

1296
02:04:57,664 --> 02:05:00,876
[ Anakin ] You're gonna pay
for all the Jedi that
you killed today, Dooku.

1297
02:05:00,959 --> 02:05:03,754
We'll take him together.
Go in slowly on the left.
I'm taking him now!

1298
02:05:03,837 --> 02:05:05,672
No, Anakin! No! No!

1299
02:05:06,298 --> 02:05:08,592
[ Anakin Screams ]

1300
02:05:12,804 --> 02:05:16,266
As you see,
my Jedi powers
are far beyond yours.

1301
02:05:16,350 --> 02:05:19,061
Now... back down.

1302
02:05:24,149 --> 02:05:25,984
I don't think so.

1303
02:05:38,914 --> 02:05:41,708
Master Kenobi,
you disappoint me.

1304
02:05:41,792 --> 02:05:43,836
<i>Yoda holds you</i>
<i>in such high esteem.</i>

1305
02:05:48,215 --> 02:05:49,716
Surely you can do better.

1306
02:05:54,179 --> 02:05:55,931
[ Moaning ]

1307
02:05:58,058 --> 02:06:00,352
[ Groaning ]

1308
02:06:00,727 --> 02:06:02,396
Are you all right?

1309
02:06:02,771 --> 02:06:04,106
Uh-huh.

1310
02:06:05,274 --> 02:06:09,027
We'd better get back to
the forward command center.
No. No.

1311
02:06:09,528 --> 02:06:12,614
Gather what troops you can.
We've got to get
to that hangar.

1312
02:06:12,698 --> 02:06:15,826
Get a transport. Hurry!
Right away.

1313
02:06:22,791 --> 02:06:24,084
[ Moaning ]

1314
02:06:28,630 --> 02:06:30,966
Ah! Ahh!

1315
02:06:38,056 --> 02:06:39,600
[ Anakin Shouts ]

1316
02:06:41,643 --> 02:06:42,978
Brave of you, boy.

1317
02:06:44,188 --> 02:06:46,481
<i>But I would have thought</i>
<i>you had learned your lesson.</i>

1318
02:06:46,565 --> 02:06:48,901
I am a slow learner.
<i>Anakin!</i>

1319
02:07:46,500 --> 02:07:49,169
[ Grunting ]

1320
02:07:50,963 --> 02:07:55,259
Master Yoda.
Count Dooku.

1321
02:07:55,801 --> 02:07:59,346
You have interfered
with our affairs
for the last time.

1322
02:08:15,612 --> 02:08:17,030
[ Growling ]

1323
02:08:30,169 --> 02:08:33,672
Powerful you have become,
Dooku.

1324
02:08:33,755 --> 02:08:36,925
The dark side
I sense in you.

1325
02:08:37,009 --> 02:08:39,970
I've become more powerful
than any Jedi.

1326
02:08:41,346 --> 02:08:42,598
Even you.

1327
02:08:57,738 --> 02:09:01,074
Much to learn
you still have.

1328
02:09:01,158 --> 02:09:04,244
It is obvious that
this contest
cannot be decided

1329
02:09:04,328 --> 02:09:06,371
by our knowledge
of the Force...

1330
02:09:08,498 --> 02:09:11,210
but by our skills
with a lightsaber.

1331
02:09:21,178 --> 02:09:22,179
[ Yelling ]

1332
02:09:52,626 --> 02:09:56,296
Fought well you have,
my old Padawan.

1333
02:09:56,380 --> 02:09:58,257
This is just the beginning.

1334
02:10:27,911 --> 02:10:31,456
[ Panting, Moaning ]

1335
02:10:33,250 --> 02:10:34,835
[ Sighing ]

1336
02:10:48,849 --> 02:10:51,226
[ Speaking In Droid Language ]

1337
02:11:06,700 --> 02:11:09,745
[ Grunts ]
[ Obi-Wan Groans ]

1338
02:11:12,956 --> 02:11:14,541
[ Padme ]
Anakin!

1339
02:12:31,159 --> 02:12:33,912
The Force is with us,
Master Sidious.

1340
02:12:33,996 --> 02:12:36,915
Welcome home,
Lord Tyranus.

1341
02:12:38,625 --> 02:12:40,669
You have done well.

1342
02:12:41,420 --> 02:12:43,547
I have good news
for you, my lord.

1343
02:12:45,048 --> 02:12:48,135
The war has begun.
Excellent.

1344
02:12:48,552 --> 02:12:51,388
Everything is going
as planned.

1345
02:13:01,315 --> 02:13:03,400
[ Obi-Wan ]
Do you believe
what Count Dooku said...

1346
02:13:03,483 --> 02:13:05,777
about Sidious
controlling the senate?

1347
02:13:05,861 --> 02:13:08,071
It doesn't feel right.

1348
02:13:08,155 --> 02:13:11,200
<i>Joined the dark side</i>
<i>Dooku has.</i>

1349
02:13:11,283 --> 02:13:14,244
Mmm. Lies, deceit,

1350
02:13:14,328 --> 02:13:18,332
creating mistrust
are his ways now.

1351
02:13:18,415 --> 02:13:22,836
<i>[ Windu ] Nevertheless,</i>
<i>I feel we should keep</i>
<i>a closer eye on the senate.</i>

1352
02:13:22,920 --> 02:13:25,005
I agree.

1353
02:13:26,215 --> 02:13:27,966
Where is your apprentice?

1354
02:13:28,258 --> 02:13:32,304
On his way to Naboo,
escorting Senator Amidala
home.

1355
02:13:33,680 --> 02:13:35,432
I have to admit
that without the clones,

1356
02:13:35,516 --> 02:13:37,309
it would not have
been a victory.

1357
02:13:37,392 --> 02:13:39,228
<i>[ Yoda ]</i>
<i>Victory?</i>

1358
02:13:40,145 --> 02:13:42,731
Victory, you say?

1359
02:13:42,814 --> 02:13:46,693
Master Obi-Wan,
not victory.

1360
02:13:48,028 --> 02:13:51,406
The shroud of
the dark side has fallen.

1361
02:13:52,866 --> 02:13:56,662
Begun the Clone War has.

